* Entity Template Version variables will be passed as [templateversion]
* argument to the MEASURE callable procedure MEASREAD_DIFF_() for
* accessing ZMS Style Record of the Entities (For Yosemite System support).
 01  ZMSPROC-TEMPLATE-VERSION   NATIVE-8 VALUE 562988609437745.
 01  ZMSDOPEN-TEMPLATE-VERSION  NATIVE-8 VALUE 1688888515624974.
* COBOL85 doesn’t support Numeric value greater than 18 digits.
* As, CPU & DISC Template Version Values require 19 digits in Decimal base,
* they are represented in Hexadecimal base here;
* else COBOL85 issues compilation errors.
* Please Note that this is not a Memory Storage Issue
* but a limitation of the COBOL85 language.
 01  ZMSCPU-TEMPLATE-VERSION    NATIVE-8 VALUE H"4001860900020060".
 01  ZMSDISC-TEMPLATE-VERSION   NATIVE-8 GLOBAL VALUE H"30079409001F0070".
* This flag will be set to "Y" if YOSEMITE Measure Datafile is being used.
 01  YOSEMITE-DATAFILE        PIC X(01) GLOBAL VALUE "N".
* MAX-VALUE-13 & MAX-VALUE-19 will be used in ON SIZE ERROR phrase.
* Depending on the size of variable undergoing Arithmetic overflow,
* one of these values will be passed to it.
* MAX-VALUE-19 equal to 9223372036854775807 (Max 19 digit value supported).
* Represented in Hex format, reason as explained for ZMSCPU-TEMPLATE-VERSION.
 01  MAX-VALUE-13       PIC 9(13) GLOBAL VALUE 9999999999999.
 01  MAX-VALUE-19       NATIVE-8  VALUE H"7FFFFFFFFFFFFFFF".
* W03, W04, W06, W07 will be divided by DIV-VALUE to get their
* most significant 19th digit, if any. Equal to 1000000000000000000.
* Represented in Hex format, reason as explained for ZMSCPU-TEMPLATE-VERSION.
 01  DIV-VALUE          NATIVE-8  VALUE H"DE0B6B3A7640000".
