 1000-INITIALIZE.
     DISPLAY VERSION-BANNER.
     DISPLAY COPYRIGHT.
     DISPLAY SPACE.
     IF DEBUG-MODE
         DISPLAY ">DEBUG-MODE enabled"
     END-IF.
     DISPLAY INFO-01.
* Check GUARDIAN version (must be at least M20)
     ENTER TAL "TOSVERSION" GIVING OSVERSION.
*     IF OSVERSION < M20
      IF OSVERSION < Q02
         MOVE COMPLETION-29 TO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
         PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
     END-IF.
* Specify parameters to FASTSORT
     ENTER "COBOL85^SET^SORT^PARAM^VALUE" OF CBL85UTL
         USING     SORT-FILE,
                   IN-FILE-COUNT,
                   (PROCESS-CEILING * SYSTEM-CEILING)
         GIVING RESULT.
     PERFORM 1010-SORT-PARAM-ERROR-CHECK.
     ENTER "COBOL85^SET^SORT^PARAM^VALUE" OF CBL85UTL
         USING     SORT-FILE,
                   MINTIME,
                   1
         GIVING RESULT.
     PERFORM 1010-SORT-PARAM-ERROR-CHECK.
* The following call can cause run-time warning diagnostic message 123
* to be issued if there is insufficient memory for a buffer. Nevertheless, the
* SORT will execute correctly. Use the MEM option on the RUN command to get
* sufficient memory.
* Cfr. COBOL85 T9257ABE 04APR92 softdoc, problems corrected 5.
*    ENTER "cobol85^set^sort^param^value" OF cbl85utl USING sort-file,
*        nowait-io, 1 GIVING result.
*    PERFORM 1010-sort-param-error-check.
     ENTER "COBOL85^SET^SORT^PARAM^VALUE" OF CBL85UTL
         USING     SORT-FILE,
                   SECOND-BUFFER,
                   1
         GIVING RESULT.
     PERFORM 1010-SORT-PARAM-ERROR-CHECK.
* Determine default volume and subvolume
     ENTER "GETSTARTUPTEXT" OF COBOLLIB USING STARTUP-PORTION-VOLUME,
         STARTUP-TEXT GIVING RESULT.
     IF RESULT NEGATIVE
         MOVE COMPLETION-01 TO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
         MOVE 1 TO ABEND-REQUIRED-FLAG
         PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
     END-IF.
     UNSTRING STARTUP-TEXT DELIMITED "." INTO DEFAULT-SYSTEM,
         DEFAULT-VOLUME, DEFAULT-SUBVOLUME.
     IF DEFAULT-SYSTEM (1:1) NOT = "\"
         MOVE DEFAULT-VOLUME TO DEFAULT-SUBVOLUME
         MOVE DEFAULT-SYSTEM TO DEFAULT-VOLUME
         MOVE SPACES TO DEFAULT-SYSTEM
     END-IF.
* Get name of control file
     ENTER "GETSTARTUPTEXT" OF COBOLLIB USING STARTUP-PORTION-STRING,
         STARTUP-TEXT GIVING RESULT.
     IF RESULT NEGATIVE
         MOVE COMPLETION-01 TO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
         MOVE 1 TO ABEND-REQUIRED-FLAG
         PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
     END-IF.
     IF RESULT ZERO
         MOVE COMPLETION-28 TO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
         PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
     END-IF.
