 2000-40-VALIDATE-CSV-LO-HI.
* CSVLO and CSVHI validation.
* Convert user supplied csvlo and csvhi to date time format.
* CSVLO must be smaller than CSVHI if supplied by user.
     IF CSVHI NOT ZERO
         ENTER TAL "INTERPRETTIMESTAMP"
           USING   CSVHI,
                   DATE-N-TIME
           GIVING RESULT-4
         MOVE CORR DATE-N-TIME TO CSVTIME
         MOVE CSVTIME TO REQ-CSVHI
     ELSE
         MOVE "NOT PROVIDED" TO REQ-CSVHI
     END-IF.
     IF CSVLO NOT ZERO
         ENTER TAL "INTERPRETTIMESTAMP"
           USING   CSVLO,
                   DATE-N-TIME
         GIVING RESULT-4
         MOVE CORR DATE-N-TIME TO CSVTIME
         MOVE CSVTIME TO REQ-CSVLO
     ELSE
        MOVE "NOT PROVIDED" TO REQ-CSVLO
     END-IF.
     IF (CSVHI NOT ZERO) AND (CSVLO NOT ZERO)
         IF CSVHI <= CSVLO
            MOVE COMPLETION-22 TO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
            PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
        END-IF
     END-IF.
