 2000-50-VALIDATE-MEASURE-FILES.
** Validate the Measure-files in the Measure-table.
    MOVE SPACES TO RUN-MEAS-FILE-ADV
                   RUN-SUM-MEASURE-TABLE
                   RUN-SUM-CSV-TABLE.
    PERFORM 2400-MEASURE-TABLE-SCAN
        VARYING TEMP-INDEX FROM 1 BY 1
        UNTIL TEMP-INDEX > MEASURE-MAX.
    IF NUM-VALID-FILES < 1
       SET C-EXIT-PROGRAM TO TRUE
       MOVE INFO-24 TO RUN-MEAS-FILE-ADV
    END-IF.
    IF DEBUG-MODE
       DISPLAY SPACE
       DISPLAY ">Measure Files Table"
       DISPLAY SPACE
       PERFORM
           VARYING TEMP-INDEX FROM 1 BY 1
           UNTIL TEMP-INDEX > MEASURE-MAX
               DISPLAY ">TABLE-INDEX   " TEMP-INDEX
               DISPLAY ">START         "
                   MEASURE-START OF MEASURE-TABLE(TEMP-INDEX)
               DISPLAY ">STOP          " MEASURE-STOP(TEMP-INDEX)
               DISPLAY ">INT           " MEASURE-INT(TEMP-INDEX)
               DISPLAY ">DATAFILE      " MEASURE-DATAFILE(TEMP-INDEX)
               DISPLAY ">DFNUM         " MEASURE-DFNUM(TEMP-INDEX)
               DISPLAY ">MEASFH        " MEASURE-MEASFH(TEMP-INDEX)
               DISPLAY ">SYSTEM-NUMBER " MEASURE-SYSTEM-NUMBER(TEMP-INDEX)
               DISPLAY ">VALID-FILE    " MEASURE-VALID-FILE(TEMP-INDEX)
               DISPLAY SPACE
       END-PERFORM
    END-IF.
    IF C-EXIT-PROGRAM
       MOVE COMPLETION-79 TO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
       PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
    END-IF.
*----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 2000-60-GET-START-STOP-TIMES.
* Convert actual start and stop times for run summary
    MOVE ZERO TO EARLIEST-START-TIME
                 LATEST-STOP-TIME.
    PERFORM
       VARYING MEASURE-INDEX FROM 1 BY 1
       UNTIL MEASURE-INDEX > MEASURE-MAX
        IF MEASURE-VALID-FILE(MEASURE-INDEX) = "Y"
           PERFORM 2000-62-START-AND-STOP
        END-IF
     END-PERFORM.
* Check if user-specified CSVHI > earliest start time.
    IF (CSVHI NOT ZERO)
      IF CSVHI <= EARLIEST-START-TIME
         MOVE COMPLETION-80 TO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
         MOVE INFO-23 TO RUN-SUM-CSV-LINE
         PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
      END-IF
    END-IF.
* Check if user-specified CSVLO > latest stop time.
    IF (CSVLO NOT ZERO)
      IF CSVLO >= LATEST-STOP-TIME
         MOVE COMPLETION-81 TO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
         MOVE INFO-23 TO RUN-SUM-CSV-LINE
         PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
      END-IF
    END-IF.
*----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 2000-62-START-AND-STOP.
    IF EARLIEST-START-TIME ZERO
       MOVE MEASURE-START OF MEASURE-TABLE(MEASURE-INDEX)
              TO EARLIEST-START-TIME
    ELSE
        IF MEASURE-START OF MEASURE-TABLE(MEASURE-INDEX)
            < EARLIEST-START-TIME
            MOVE MEASURE-START OF MEASURE-TABLE(MEASURE-INDEX)
               TO EARLIEST-START-TIME
        END-IF
    END-IF.
    IF LATEST-STOP-TIME  < MEASURE-STOP(MEASURE-INDEX)
       MOVE MEASURE-STOP(MEASURE-INDEX) TO LATEST-STOP-TIME
    END-IF.
*----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 2000-70-GET-POSSIBLE-CSV-COUNT.
* Compute the number of CSV files possible.
* Set latest-stop-time to min(csvhi, latest-stop-time)
   IF CSVHI NOT ZERO
      IF CSVHI < LATEST-STOP-TIME
         MOVE CSVHI TO LATEST-STOP-TIME
      END-IF
   END-IF.
* Set earliest-start-time to max(csvlo, measure-start(1))
  IF CSVLO NOT ZERO
     IF CSVLO > EARLIEST-START-TIME
        MOVE CSVLO TO EARLIEST-START-TIME
     END-IF
  END-IF.
    ENTER TAL "INTERPRETTIMESTAMP"
       USING   EARLIEST-START-TIME,
               DATE-N-TIME
       GIVING RESULT-4.
    MOVE CORR DATE-N-TIME TO CSVTIME.
    MOVE CSVTIME TO ACT-CSVLO.
    ENTER TAL "INTERPRETTIMESTAMP"
       USING   LATEST-STOP-TIME,
               DATE-N-TIME
       GIVING RESULT-4.
    MOVE CORR DATE-N-TIME TO CSVTIME.
    MOVE CSVTIME TO ACT-CSVHI.
* Calculate the number of csv files possible. (LCM is the interval duration).
  COMPUTE TEMP-STORE = LATEST-STOP-TIME - EARLIEST-START-TIME.
  MOVE ZERO TO REM.
* GAG 98/11/23.   Check below was changed to > 0 instead of >= because of div by 0.
  IF LCM > 0
     DIVIDE TEMP-STORE BY LCM
        GIVING NUM-CSVS-POSSIBLE
        REMAINDER REM
     IF REM > ZERO AND NUM-CSVS-POSSIBLE = ZERO
        MOVE 1 TO NUM-CSVS-POSSIBLE
     END-IF
  ELSE
     MOVE 1 TO NUM-CSVS-POSSIBLE
  END-IF.
  IF NUM-CSVS-POSSIBLE > MAX-CSVS-POSSIBLE
     MOVE MAX-CSVS-POSSIBLE TO NUM-CSVS-POSSIBLE
  END-IF.
*----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 2000-80-GET-USER-CSV-COUNT.
* Check user specified number of csv files.
* If the user specifies max. possible csv files, generate the number as
* computed above. Otherwise, move the parameter to a numeric field and check
* the value against max possible. If it is greater than or equal to max
* possible, generate max possible, else re-compute the lcm to use it as
* the intervals for which the measure data files will be read.
  MOVE NUMBER-CSVS-ALPHA TO REQ-NUM-CSV.
  MOVE 1 TO NUM-OF-LCMS.
  IF C-DEFAULT-CSVS
     MOVE 1 TO NUM-CSVS-ACTUAL
  ELSE
     IF C-MAX-CSVS
         MOVE NUM-CSVS-POSSIBLE TO NUM-CSVS-ACTUAL
     ELSE
         PERFORM 2001-GET-NUMBER-CSVS
         MOVE NUMBER-CSVS TO NUM-CSVS-ACTUAL
         IF NUMBER-CSVS > 1
             IF NUMBER-CSVS < NUM-CSVS-POSSIBLE
*                Calculate the number of lcm(intervals) to form these files.
*                If the remainder is not zero, check if incrementing the
*                number of lcms will still result in the last csv file
*                starting before the latest stop time.
                 DIVIDE NUM-CSVS-POSSIBLE BY NUMBER-CSVS
                     GIVING NUM-OF-LCMS REMAINDER REM
                 IF (REM NOT ZERO) AND (LCM > 0)
                     COMPUTE TEMP-START =  EARLIEST-START-TIME +
                          ((NUM-OF-LCMS + 1)  * LCM * NUMBER-CSVS)
                     IF TEMP-START < LATEST-STOP-TIME
                         ADD 1 TO NUM-OF-LCMS
                     END-IF
                 END-IF
             ELSE
                MOVE NUM-CSVS-POSSIBLE TO NUM-CSVS-ACTUAL
             END-IF
         END-IF
     END-IF
  END-IF.
*  Move to run summary.
  MOVE NUM-CSVS-ACTUAL TO ACT-NUM-CSV.
  MOVE NUMBER-CSVS-ALPHA TO REQ-NUM-CSV.
  IF C-MAX-CSVS
     MOVE "MAX" TO REQ-NUM-CSV
  ELSE
    IF C-DEFAULT-CSVS
       MOVE "DEF" TO REQ-NUM-CSV
    END-IF
  END-IF.
  MOVE NUM-CSVS-POSSIBLE TO POSS-NUM-CSV.
  DISPLAY "Number of CSV Data files : ", ACT-NUM-CSV.
*----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 2000-90-GET-CSVDATA-NAMES.
* If no CSVDATA keyword was detected, supply the default name
     IF CSVDATA = LOW-VALUES MOVE "CSVDA" TO CSVDATA.
* Determine the position in the variable csvdata to append the file number.
* This is done by scanning the var. CSVDATA backwards till the first non-space
* character and "." character are found. The difference between the two byte
* locations is computed. If the difference is > 6 then the location for the
* number is set to the 6th byte from the location of "." character. If not the
* difference +1 from the location of "." is the byte position.
     MOVE ZERO TO LOC1, LOC2.
     PERFORM VARYING LOC-INDEX FROM 35 BY -1 UNTIL LOC-INDEX < 1
        IF LOC1  ZERO
           IF CSVDATA(LOC-INDEX:1) NOT = SPACES
               MOVE LOC-INDEX TO LOC1
           END-IF
        END-IF
        IF LOC2 ZERO
           IF CSVDATA(LOC-INDEX:1) = "."
              MOVE LOC-INDEX TO LOC2
           END-IF
        END-IF
      END-PERFORM.
      COMPUTE LOC-DIFF = LOC1 - LOC2.
      IF LOC-DIFF > 5
         COMPUTE POS = LOC2 + 6
      ELSE
         COMPUTE POS = LOC2 + LOC-DIFF + 1
      END-IF.
*----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 2000-100-APPLICATION-NAME.
* Application name is required
     IF I03 = LOW-VALUES
         MOVE COMPLETION-05 TO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
         PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
     END-IF.
*----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 2000-110-PREPARE-CATEGORIES.
* TITLE-TABLE must be completely filled out (up to TITLE-MAX)
     SET TITLE-INDEX TO 1.
     SEARCH TITLE-TABLE
         WHEN TITLE-TYPE (TITLE-INDEX) = SPACE
             MOVE ZERO TO SCRATCH-NATIVE2
             MOVE TITLE-NUMBER OF TITLE-TABLE (TITLE-INDEX) TO SCRATCH-X
             MOVE SCRATCH-NATIVE2 TO NUMBER-DISPLAY
             STRING COMPLETION-46  DELIMITED SIZE
                    SPACE          DELIMITED SIZE
                    NUMBER-DISPLAY DELIMITED SIZE
                    INTO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
             PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
     END-SEARCH.
* Sort WKLD-TABLE in ascending order using the Heapsort algorithm
     COPY HEAPSORT REPLACING
         I       BY HEAP-I
         IR      BY HEAP-IR
         J       BY HEAP-J
         L       BY HEAP-L
         N       BY WKLD-MAX
         INDEX-1 BY WKLD-INDEX
         INDEX-2 BY WKLD-INDEX-2
         TABLE   BY WKLD-TABLE
         TEMP    BY WKLD-TEMP
         KEY     BY WKLD-SORT-KEY.
* Sort TITLE-TABLE in ascending order according to TITLE-NUMBER using the
* Heapsort algorithm
     COPY HEAPSORT REPLACING
         I       BY HEAP-I
         IR      BY HEAP-IR
         J       BY HEAP-J
         L       BY HEAP-L
         N       BY TITLE-MAX
         INDEX-1 BY TITLE-INDEX
         INDEX-2 BY TITLE-INDEX-2
         TABLE   BY TITLE-SORT-MOVE
         TEMP    BY TITLE-TEMP
         KEY     BY TITLE-NUMBER.
*----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 2000-120-ADD-CAT-98.
* Add category 98 (_OTHER)
     ADD 1 TO TITLE-MAX, WKLD-MAX.
     SET TITLE-INDEX TO TITLE-MAX.
     SET WKLD-INDEX TO WKLD-MAX.
     MOVE 98 TO SCRATCH-NATIVE2.
     MOVE SCRATCH-X TO TITLE-NUMBER OF TITLE-TABLE (TITLE-INDEX),
         WKLD-NUMBER (WKLD-INDEX).
     MOVE "O" TO TITLE-TYPE (TITLE-INDEX).
     MOVE "_OTHER" TO TITLE-NAME (TITLE-INDEX).
     MOVE WC-ASTERISK-NUM  TO WKLD-PIN              (WKLD-INDEX),
                              WKLD-SYSTEM           (WKLD-INDEX),
                              WKLD-CPU              (WKLD-INDEX).
     MOVE WC-ASTERISK-ALFA TO WKLD-PROCESS-NAME     (WKLD-INDEX),
                              WKLD-PROGRAM-FILENAME (WKLD-INDEX),
                              WKLD-PROGRAM-FILENAME (WKLD-INDEX) (9:1),
                              WKLD-PROGRAM-FILENAME (WKLD-INDEX) (17:1),
                              WKLD-USERID-FLAG      (WKLD-INDEX).
*----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 2000-130-ADD-CAT-99.
* Add category 99 (_ERROR)
     ADD 1 TO TITLE-MAX, WKLD-MAX.
     SET TITLE-INDEX TO TITLE-MAX.
     SET WKLD-INDEX TO WKLD-MAX.
     MOVE 99 TO SCRATCH-NATIVE2.
     MOVE SCRATCH-X TO TITLE-NUMBER OF TITLE-TABLE (TITLE-INDEX),
         WKLD-NUMBER (WKLD-INDEX).
     MOVE "O" TO TITLE-TYPE (TITLE-INDEX).
     MOVE "_ERROR" TO TITLE-NAME (TITLE-INDEX).
*----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 2000-140-INITIALISE-CSV-AREAS.
* Initialize CSV-W-BINARY
     PERFORM
         VARYING TITLE-INDEX FROM 1 BY 1
         UNTIL TITLE-INDEX > TITLE-MAX
         INITIALIZE CSV-W-BINARY (TITLE-INDEX)
     END-PERFORM.
*----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 2000-150-DEBUG.
* Display debug-fields
     IF DEBUG-MODE DISPLAY ">MEASURE-MAX: ", MEASURE-MAX,
                           " VERSION-MAX: ", VERSION-MAX,
                           " WKLD-MAX: "   , WKLD-MAX   ,
                           " TITLE-MAX: "  , TITLE-MAX  ,
                           " TXN-MAX: "    , TXN-MAX    ,
                           " SYSTEM-MAX: " , SYSTEM-MAX
     END-IF.
*----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 2001-GET-NUMBER-CSVS.
     UNSTRING NUMBER-CSVS-ALPHA DELIMITED SPACES INTO NUMBER-CSVS.
     IF NUMBER-CSVS NOT NUMERIC
        MOVE COMPLETION-83 TO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
        PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
     ELSE
        IF NUMBER-CSVS < 1
           MOVE COMPLETION-84 TO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
           PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
        END-IF
     END-IF.
*----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 2005-AUDIT-YES.
     ENTER TAL "FNAMEEXPAND"
         USING     REPORT-LOCATION,
                   INTERNAL-FILENAME,
                   DEFAULT-NAMES
         GIVING RESULT.
     IF RESULT ZERO
        MOVE COMPLETION-64 TO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
        PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
     END-IF.
     ENTER "COBOLASSIGN" OF COBOLLIB
         USING     SPOOLER-FILE,
                   PART1 OF INTERNAL-FILENAME
         GIVING RESULT.
     IF RESULT NOT ZERO
        MOVE RESULT TO NUMBER-DISPLAY
        STRING COMPLETION-65  DELIMITED SIZE
            SPACE          DELIMITED SIZE
            NUMBER-DISPLAY DELIMITED SIZE
            INTO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
        PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
     END-IF.
* Open the Spooler (level 3)
     ENTER "COBOL85^SPECIAL^OPEN" OF CBL85UTL
         USING     SPOOLER-FILE,
                   OMITTED,
                   ZERO,
                   OMITTED,
                   1,
                   1,
                   QUALIFIERS
         GIVING RESULT.
     IF RESULT NOT ZERO
        MOVE RESULT TO NUMBER-DISPLAY
        STRING COMPLETION-66  DELIMITED SIZE
               SPACE          DELIMITED SIZE
               NUMBER-DISPLAY DELIMITED SIZE
               INTO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
        PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
     END-IF.
     SET C-SPOOL-FILE-OPEN TO TRUE.
*----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 2010-READ-LOOP.
* Read and process the next record in the control file
     READ CONTROL-FILE
       AT END
         SET CONTROL-FILE-EOF TO TRUE
     END-READ.
* Process record but ignore comment lines
* Count the number of blank spaces before the keyword in the control-file-
* record. Remove the blank spaces by left-shifting the record by the counted
* number of characters. Soln 10-001222-8124.
     IF NOT CONTROL-FILE-EOF
       MOVE 0 TO COUNT-OF-BLANKS
       IF CONTROL-FILE-RECORD (1:1) = SPACES
         PERFORM VARYING TEMP-COUNTER FROM 1 BY 1
            UNTIL CONTROL-FILE-RECORD (TEMP-COUNTER : 1) NOT = SPACES
               OR TEMP-COUNTER >= 80
           ADD 1 TO COUNT-OF-BLANKS
         END-PERFORM
         IF COUNT-OF-BLANKS < 80
          MOVE SPACES TO TEMP-RECORD-BUFFER
          MOVE CONTROL-FILE-RECORD (COUNT-OF-BLANKS + 1 : 80 - COUNT-OF-BLANKS)
          TO TEMP-RECORD-BUFFER (1 : 80 - COUNT-OF-BLANKS)
          MOVE SPACES TO CONTROL-FILE-RECORD
          MOVE TEMP-RECORD-BUFFER TO CONTROL-FILE-RECORD
         END-IF
       END-IF
     END-IF.
* End of code changes of Soln 10-001222-8124.
     IF NOT CONTROL-FILE-EOF
         IF NOT CONTROL-FILE-RECORD (1:1) COMMENT-CHARS
           PERFORM 2020-PROCESS-CONTROL-RECORD
         END-IF
     END-IF.
*----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 2020-PROCESS-CONTROL-RECORD.
* Upshift all alphabetic characters
     INSPECT CONTROL-FILE-RECORD CONVERTING
         "abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz" TO "ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ".
* Get the different parts of the record
     MOVE SPACES TO input-fields.
     UNSTRING CONTROL-FILE-RECORD DELIMITED ALL SPACE INTO
         KEYWORD, PARAMETER1, PARAMETER2, PARAMETER3, PARAMETER4, PARAMETER5, PARAMETER6.
* Check for keywords
     IF KEYWORD(1:4) = "WKLD" OR "PCAT"
         MOVE "WKLD" TO CASE-KEYWORD
     ELSE
         IF KEYWORD(1:5) = "TITLE"
             MOVE "TITLE" TO CASE-KEYWORD
         ELSE
             MOVE KEYWORD TO CASE-KEYWORD
         END-IF
     END-IF.
     EVALUATE CASE-KEYWORD
       WHEN "MEASURE"    PERFORM 2100-MEASURE-INPUT
       WHEN "CSVDATA"    PERFORM 2110-CSVDATA-INPUT
       WHEN "CSVLO"      PERFORM 2120-CSVLO-INPUT
       WHEN "CSVHI"      PERFORM 2130-CSVHI-INPUT
       WHEN "APPL"       PERFORM 2140-APPL-INPUT
       WHEN "WKLD"       PERFORM 2160-WKLD-INPUT
       WHEN "TITLE"      PERFORM 2170-TITLE-INPUT
       WHEN "TXN"        PERFORM 2180-TXN-INPUT
       WHEN "REPORT"     PERFORM 2190-REPORT-INPUT
       WHEN "CONVERTTO"  PERFORM 2200-CONVERTTO-INPUT
       WHEN "CPUFACTOR"  PERFORM 2220-CPUFACTOR-INPUT
       WHEN "NUMCSVS"    PERFORM 2230-NUMCSVS-INPUT
* Soln 10-020415-8203 : start
       WHEN "DISKCONVERTTO"  PERFORM 2240-DISKCONVERTTO-INPUT
       WHEN "DISKFACTOR"     PERFORM 2250-DISKFACTOR-INPUT
       WHEN "ACTUALDISK42"   PERFORM 2260-ACTUALDISK42-INPUT
       WHEN "ACTUALDISK43"   PERFORM 2270-ACTUALDISK43-INPUT
       WHEN "ACTUALDISK44"   PERFORM 2280-ACTUALDISK44-INPUT
* Soln 10-020415-8203 : END
*------------MeasTCM Yosemite Change----Start-----------
* For JBOD (SubType = 53) Disk models.
       WHEN "ACTUALDISK53"   PERFORM 2290-ACTUALDISK53-INPUT
*------------MeasTCM Yosemite Change-----End------------
* Start of code change for CEP RFE.
* Added for SAS disk models (Subtype = 51).
       WHEN "ACTUALDISK51"   PERFORM 2450-ACTUALDISK51-INPUT
* Added for XP disk (Subtype = 52).
       WHEN "ACTUALDISK52"   PERFORM 2460-ACTUALDISK52-INPUT
       WHEN "XPDISKFACTOR"   PERFORM 2470-XPDISKFACTOR-INPUT
       WHEN "NUMTMFTRAIL"    PERFORM 2500-NUMTMFTRAIL-INPUT
* End of code change for CEP RFE.
       WHEN OTHER        PERFORM 2210-INVALID-KEYWORD
     END-EVALUATE.
*----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 2100-MEASURE-INPUT.
* Keyword MEASURE detected
* Expand the specified data file name to the standard 12-word internal form
     ENTER TAL "FNAMEEXPAND"
       USING   PARAMETER1,
               INTERNAL-FILENAME,
               DEFAULT-NAMES
       GIVING RESULT.
     IF RESULT ZERO
         MOVE COMPLETION-31 TO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
         PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
     END-IF.
* Add data file name to MEASURE-TABLE
     SET MEASURE-INDEX TO 1.
     SEARCH MEASURE-TABLE
         END
             PERFORM
                 IF MEASURE-MAX = MEASURE-CEILING
*                      Too many measure data files
                     MOVE COMPLETION-57 TO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
                     PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
                 END-IF
                 ADD 1 TO MEASURE-MAX
                 SET MEASURE-INDEX TO MEASURE-MAX
                 MOVE INTERNAL-FILENAME TO MEASURE-DATAFILE (MEASURE-INDEX)
                 MOVE PARAMETER1 TO MEASURE-EXTERNAL-NAME (MEASURE-INDEX)
                 MOVE ZERO TO MEASURE-DFNUM (MEASURE-INDEX)
             END-PERFORM
         WHEN MEASURE-DATAFILE (MEASURE-INDEX) = INTERNAL-FILENAME
*             Duplicate file name detected
             MOVE COMPLETION-32 TO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
             PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
     END-SEARCH.
* Check measfh file name
     IF PARAMETER2 = "!" OR PARAMETER2 = SPACES
         MOVE SPACES TO PARAMETER2, MEASURE-MEASFH (MEASURE-INDEX)
     END-IF.
     IF PARAMETER2 NOT = SPACES
*        Expand the specified measfh file name to the standard 12-word
*        internal form
         ENTER TAL "FNAMEEXPAND"
           USING   PARAMETER2,
                   INTERNAL-FILENAME,
                   DEFAULT-NAMES
           GIVING RESULT
         IF RESULT ZERO
             MOVE COMPLETION-48 TO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
             PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
         END-IF
*        Add measfh file name to MEASURE-TABLE
         MOVE INTERNAL-FILENAME TO MEASURE-MEASFH (MEASURE-INDEX)
     END-IF.
* Open measure data file
     DISPLAY INFO-04, SPACE, PARAMETER1.
     IF MEASURE-MEASFH (MEASURE-INDEX) = SPACES
         ENTER TAL "MEASOPEN"
           USING   MEASURE-DATAFILE (MEASURE-INDEX),
                   MEASURE-DFNUM (MEASURE-INDEX),
                   ZERO,
                   -1
           GIVING RESULT
     ELSE
         ENTER TAL "MEASOPEN"
           USING   MEASURE-DATAFILE (MEASURE-INDEX),
                   MEASURE-DFNUM (MEASURE-INDEX),
                   ZERO,
                   -1,
                   MEASURE-MEASFH (MEASURE-INDEX)
           GIVING RESULT
     END-IF.
     IF RESULT NOT ZERO
         MOVE RESULT TO NUMBER-DISPLAY
         STRING COMPLETION-49  DELIMITED SIZE
                SPACE          DELIMITED SIZE
                NUMBER-DISPLAY DELIMITED SIZE
                INTO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
         MOVE 1 TO ABEND-REQUIRED-FLAG
         PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
     END-IF.
* Determine version of measure data file and system name
     ENTER TAL "MEASGETVERSION"
           USING   MEASURE-DATAFILE (MEASURE-INDEX),
                   OMITTED,
                   DFVERSION,
                   ENTITY-LENGTH-BUFFER,
                   ENT-BUF-LEN,
                   SYSNAME
           GIVING RESULT.
     IF RESULT NOT ZERO
         MOVE RESULT TO NUMBER-DISPLAY
         STRING COMPLETION-51  DELIMITED SIZE
                SPACE          DELIMITED SIZE
                NUMBER-DISPLAY DELIMITED SIZE
                INTO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
         MOVE 1 TO ABEND-REQUIRED-FLAG
         PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
     END-IF.
* Data file version has to be at least G02
*    IF DFVERSION < C10
     IF DFVERSION < G02
         MOVE COMPLETION-30 TO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
         PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
     END-IF.
* Note highest guardian series for power conversion formulas.
* Need either C, or D for D and above.
*Removed as part of CEP RFE
*     IF DFVERSION < D00
*        MOVE "C" TO CONVERT-GUARDIAN-SAVE
*     ELSE
*        MOVE "D" TO CONVERT-GUARDIAN-SAVE
*     END-IF.
*     IF CONVERT-GUARDIAN-SAVE = "D"
*         MOVE "D" TO CONVERT-GUARDIAN-VERSION
*     END-IF.
*------------MeasTCM Yosemite Change----Start-----------
* Check for YOSEMITE Measure Datafile.
* Modified IF condition for Soln:10-100304-8526
    IF DFVERSION >= H01 AND DFVERSION <= H06
        MOVE "Y" TO YOSEMITE-DATAFILE
    ELSE
        MOVE "N" TO YOSEMITE-DATAFILE
    END-IF.
*------------MeasTCM Yosemite Change-----End------------
* Obtain pseudo system number
     SET SYSTEM-INDEX TO 1.
     SEARCH SYSTEM-TABLE
         END
*            System does not exist yet: insert it into SYSTEM-TABLE
             PERFORM 2102-SYSTEM
         WHEN SYSTEM-NAME OF SYSTEM-TABLE (SYSTEM-INDEX) = SYSNAME
*            Check to make sure that DFVERSION equals SYSTEM-VERSION
             IF DFVERSION NOT = SYSTEM-VERSION (SYSTEM-INDEX)
                 MOVE COMPLETION-60 TO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
                 PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
             END-IF
     END-SEARCH.
     SET MEASURE-SYSTEM-NUMBER (MEASURE-INDEX) TO SYSTEM-INDEX.
* Get the start and stop times and interval for this Measure data file
     ENTER TAL "MEASREADCONF"
           USING   MEASURE-DFNUM(MEASURE-INDEX),
                   MEASREAD-BUFFER,
                   MEASREAD-BUFFER-LENGTH,
                   BYTESRET,
                   MEASURE-START OF MEASURE-TABLE(MEASURE-INDEX),
                   MEASURE-STOP(MEASURE-INDEX),
                   MEASURE-INT(MEASURE-INDEX),
                   ENTITIES,
                   CTRSPACE,
                   DFVERSION
           GIVING  RESULT.
* Display debug fields
     IF DEBUG-MODE
         DISPLAY ">MEASURE "       , MEASURE-MAX          ,
                 ": dfnum "        , MEASURE-DFNUM (MEASURE-INDEX),
                 ", system number ", MEASURE-SYSTEM-NUMBER (MEASURE-INDEX)
     END-IF.
*----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 2102-SYSTEM.
     ADD 1 TO SYSTEM-MAX.
     IF SYSTEM-MAX > SYSTEM-CEILING
*       Too many different system names; this should never
*       occur as long as  MEASURE-CEILING = SYSTEM-CEILING
         STRING COMPLETION-54     DELIMITED SIZE
                " (SYSTEM-TABLE)" DELIMITED SIZE
                INTO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
         MOVE 1 TO ABEND-REQUIRED-FLAG
         PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
     END-IF.
     SET SYSTEM-INDEX TO SYSTEM-MAX.
     MOVE SYSNAME TO SYSTEM-NAME OF SYSTEM-TABLE (SYSTEM-INDEX).
     MOVE DFVERSION TO SYSTEM-VERSION (SYSTEM-INDEX).
*    Display debug fields
     IF DEBUG-MODE
         DISPLAY ">SYSTEM "          , SYSTEM-MAX     ,
                 ": system name "    , SYSNAME        ,
                 ", measure version ", DFVERSION
     END-IF.
*    Check if measurement version is already defined in
*    VERSION-TABLE; if not, insert it !
     SET version-index TO 1.
     SEARCH VERSION-TABLE
         END
             PERFORM 2104-MEASURE-VERSION
         WHEN VERSION-VALUE (VERSION-INDEX) = DFVERSION
             CONTINUE
     END-SEARCH.
*----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 2104-MEASURE-VERSION.
     ADD 1 TO VERSION-MAX.
     IF VERSION-MAX > VERSION-CEILING
*        Too many different measure versions
         STRING COMPLETION-54      DELIMITED SIZE
                " (VERSION-TABLE)" DELIMITED SIZE
                INTO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
         MOVE 1 TO ABEND-REQUIRED-FLAG
         PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
     END-IF.
     SET VERSION-INDEX TO VERSION-MAX.
     MOVE DFVERSION TO VERSION-VALUE (VERSION-INDEX).
     MOVE CORR ENTITY-LENGTHS TO
         VERSION-ENTITY-LENGTHS (VERSION-INDEX).
*    Display debug fields
     IF DEBUG-MODE
         DISPLAY
             ">VERSION ", VERSION-MAX  ,
             ": "       ,
             VERSION-VALUE (VERSION-INDEX)
     END-IF.
*----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 2110-CSVDATA-INPUT.
* Keyword CSVDATA detected
* Check for duplicates
     IF CSVDATA NOT = LOW-VALUES
         MOVE COMPLETION-06 TO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
         PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
     END-IF.
     IF PARAMETER1 = SPACES OR PARAMETER1 (1:1) = "!"
         MOVE COMPLETION-47 TO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
         PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
     END-IF.
     MOVE PARAMETER1 TO CSVDATA.
* Display debug fields
     IF DEBUG-MODE
         DISPLAY ">CSVDATA: ", CSVDATA
     END-IF.
*----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 2120-CSVLO-INPUT.
* Keyword CSVLO detected
* Check for duplicates
     IF CSVLO NOT ZERO
         MOVE COMPLETION-07 TO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
         PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
     END-IF.
* Check that date and time are numeric
     MOVE PARAMETER1 TO CSVTIME.
     IF    YEAR    OF CSVTIME NOT NUMERIC OR
           MONTH   OF CSVTIME NOT NUMERIC OR
           DDAY    OF CSVTIME NOT NUMERIC OR
           HOURS   OF CSVTIME NOT NUMERIC OR
           MINUTES OF CSVTIME NOT NUMERIC OR
           SECONDS OF CSVTIME NOT NUMERIC
         MOVE COMPLETION-08 TO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
         PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
     END-IF.
* Compute timestamp
     MOVE CORR CSVTIME TO DATE-N-TIME.
     ENTER TAL "COMPUTETIMESTAMP" USING DATE-N-TIME, RESULT GIVING CSVLO.
     IF RESULT NOT ZERO
         MOVE RESULT TO NUMBER-DISPLAY
         STRING COMPLETION-25  DELIMITED SIZE
                SPACE          DELIMITED SIZE
                NUMBER-DISPLAY DELIMITED SIZE
                INTO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
*         MOVE 1 TO ABEND-REQUIRED-FLAG
         PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
     END-IF.
* Display debug fields
     IF DEBUG-MODE
        MOVE CORR CSVTIME TO I04
        MOVE CORR CSVTIME TO I05
        DISPLAY ">CSVLO: ", I04, SPACE, I05
     END-IF.
*----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 2130-CSVHI-INPUT.
* Keyword CSVHI detected
* Check for duplicates
     IF CSVHI NOT ZERO
         MOVE COMPLETION-09 TO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
         PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
     END-IF.
* Check that date and time are numeric
     MOVE PARAMETER1 TO CSVTIME.
     IF    YEAR    OF CSVTIME NOT NUMERIC OR
           MONTH   OF CSVTIME NOT NUMERIC OR
           DDAY    OF CSVTIME NOT NUMERIC OR
           HOURS   OF CSVTIME NOT NUMERIC OR
           MINUTES OF CSVTIME NOT NUMERIC OR
           SECONDS OF CSVTIME NOT NUMERIC
         MOVE COMPLETION-10 TO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
         PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
     END-IF.
* Compute timestamp
     MOVE CORR CSVTIME TO DATE-N-TIME.
     ENTER TAL "COMPUTETIMESTAMP" USING DATE-N-TIME, RESULT GIVING CSVHI.
     IF RESULT NOT ZERO
         MOVE RESULT TO NUMBER-DISPLAY
         STRING COMPLETION-26  DELIMITED SIZE
                SPACE          DELIMITED SIZE
                NUMBER-DISPLAY DELIMITED SIZE
                INTO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
*         MOVE 1 TO ABEND-REQUIRED-FLAG
         PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
     END-IF.
* Display debug fields
     IF DEBUG-MODE
        MOVE CORR CSVTIME TO I06
        MOVE CORR CSVTIME TO I07
        DISPLAY ">CSVHI: ", I06, SPACE, I07
     END-IF.
*----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 2140-APPL-INPUT.
* Keyword APPL detected
* Check for duplicates
     IF I03 NOT = LOW-VALUES
         MOVE COMPLETION-11 TO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
         PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
     END-IF.
     IF PARAMETER1 = SPACES OR PARAMETER1 (1:1) = "!"
         MOVE COMPLETION-12 TO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
         PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
     END-IF.
* Application name should start with a letter
     IF PARAMETER1 (1:1) < "A" OR PARAMETER1 (1:1) > "Z"
         MOVE COMPLETION-73 TO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
         PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
     END-IF.
*Start of Change-Validation Check for 20 chars
     UNSTRING PARAMETER1 DELIMITED BY ALL SPACES INTO APPL-INPUT-T1
     IF APPL-INPUT-T1 (1:1) NOT EQUAL SPACES
         MOVE COMPLETION-73 TO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
         PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
     END-IF.
*End of Change-Validation Check for 20 chars
* Move result to CSV I-record and P-TITLE-1
     MOVE PARAMETER1 TO I03, P-APPLICATION.
* Display debug fields
     IF DEBUG-MODE DISPLAY ">APPL: ", I03.
*----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 2160-WKLD-INPUT.
* Keyword WKLD or PCAT detected
* WKLD keywords must precede TITLE keywords
     IF TITLE-DETECTED
         MOVE COMPLETION-45 TO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
         PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
     END-IF.
     ADD 1 TO WKLD-MAX.
* Maximum (WKLD-CEILING - 2) WKLD entries are allowed in the control file
     IF WKLD-MAX > WKLD-CEILING - 2
         MOVE COMPLETION-58 TO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
         PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
     END-IF.
* Obtain category number
     MOVE KEYWORD (5:2) TO SCRATCH-99.
     IF SCRATCH-99 NOT NUMERIC
         STRING COMPLETION-23 DELIMITED SIZE
                SPACE         DELIMITED SIZE
                KEYWORD (5:2) DELIMITED SIZE
                INTO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
         PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
     END-IF.
* Maximum user-defined category number is 97
     IF SCRATCH-99 > 97
         STRING COMPLETION-18 DELIMITED SIZE
                SPACE         DELIMITED SIZE
                KEYWORD (5:2) DELIMITED SIZE
                INTO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
         PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
     END-IF.
* Store new WKLD-NUMBER
     SET WKLD-INDEX TO WKLD-MAX.
     MOVE SCRATCH-99 TO SCRATCH-NATIVE2.
     MOVE SCRATCH-X TO WKLD-NUMBER (WKLD-INDEX).
* Check if corresponding TITLE-NUMBER already exists.
     SET TITLE-INDEX TO 1.
     SEARCH TITLE-TABLE
         END
             PERFORM 2161-NEW-TITLE
         WHEN WKLD-NUMBER (WKLD-INDEX) =
                TITLE-NUMBER OF TITLE-TABLE (TITLE-INDEX)
             NEXT SENTENCE
     END-SEARCH.
* Display debug field
     IF DEBUG-MODE
         DISPLAY ">WKLD", KEYWORD (5:2), " :" NO ADVANCING
     END-IF.
* Split PARAMETER1 into system, CPU, PIN
     MOVE SPACES TO WKLD-LINE, INTERNAL-FILENAME.
*Start of Change-Validation Check for 8 chars Node name
*     UNSTRING PARAMETER1 DELIMITED ",", OR SPACE INTO L-SYSTEM, L-CPU, L-PIN.
     UNSTRING PARAMETER1 DELIMITED ",", OR SPACE INTO TEMP-L-SYSTEM, L-CPU, L-PIN.
      IF TEMP-L-SYSTEM (9:1) NOT EQUAL SPACES
          PERFORM 2300-INVALID-NODE-NAME
      END-IF
      MOVE TEMP-L-SYSTEM TO L-SYSTEM
*End of Change-Validation Check for 8 chars Node name
* Check if system equals "*", in that case
* move WC-ASTERISK-NUM to WKLD-SYSTEM
     IF L-SYSTEM = "*"
         MOVE WC-ASTERISK-NUM TO WKLD-SYSTEM (WKLD-INDEX)
     ELSE
*        Check for a valid system name
         PERFORM 2162-SYSTEM
     END-IF.
* Display debug field
     IF DEBUG-MODE
         DISPLAY SPACE, WKLD-SYSTEM (WKLD-INDEX) NO ADVANCING
     END-IF.
* Check if CPU equals "*", in that case move WC-ASTERISK-NUM to WKLD-CPU
     IF L-CPU = " *"
         MOVE WC-ASTERISK-NUM TO WKLD-CPU (WKLD-INDEX)
     ELSE
*        Check for a valid CPU number
         PERFORM 2163-CPU
     END-IF.
* Display debug field
     IF DEBUG-MODE
         DISPLAY SPACE, WKLD-CPU (WKLD-INDEX) NO ADVANCING
     END-IF.
* Check if PIN equals "*", in that case move WC-ASTERISK-NUM to WKLD-PIN
     IF L-PIN = "    *"
         MOVE WC-ASTERISK-NUM TO WKLD-PIN (WKLD-INDEX)
     ELSE
*        Check for a valid PIN number
         PERFORM 2164-PIN
     END-IF.
* Display debug field
     IF DEBUG-MODE
         DISPLAY SPACE, SCRATCH-99999 NO ADVANCING
     END-IF.
* Do an elementary check for a valid process name
     IF PARAMETER2 NOT WC-FILENAME
         STRING COMPLETION-36 DELIMITED SIZE
                SPACE         DELIMITED SIZE
                KEYWORD (5:2) DELIMITED SIZE
                INTO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
         PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
     END-IF.
* Store WKLD-PROCESS-NAME
     MOVE PARAMETER2 TO WKLD-PROCESS-NAME (WKLD-INDEX).
* Replace * by WC-ASTERISK-ALFA and ? by WC-QUESTION
     INSPECT WKLD-PROCESS-NAME (WKLD-INDEX)
         REPLACING FIRST "*" BY WC-ASTERISK-ALFA, ALL "?" BY WC-QUESTION.
* Display debug field
     IF DEBUG-MODE
         DISPLAY SPACE, PARAMETER2 (1:8) NO ADVANCING
     END-IF.
* Split PARAMETER3 into the different file name parts
     UNSTRING PARAMETER3 DELIMITED "." INTO PART1 OF INTERNAL-FILENAME,
         PART2 OF INTERNAL-FILENAME, PART3 OF INTERNAL-FILENAME.
* Do an elementary check for a valid file name
     IF    INTERNAL-FILENAME NOT WC-FILENAME   OR
           PART1 OF INTERNAL-FILENAME = SPACES OR
           PART2 OF INTERNAL-FILENAME = SPACES OR
           PART3 OF INTERNAL-FILENAME = SPACES
         STRING COMPLETION-37 DELIMITED SIZE
                SPACE         DELIMITED SIZE
                KEYWORD (5:2) DELIMITED SIZE
                INTO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
         PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
     END-IF.
* Store WKLD-PROGRAM-FILENAME
     MOVE INTERNAL-FILENAME TO WKLD-PROGRAM-FILENAME (WKLD-INDEX).
* Replace * by WC-ASTERISK-ALFA and ? by WC-QUESTION
     INSPECT WKLD-PROGRAM-FILENAME (WKLD-INDEX)
         REPLACING ALL "*" BY WC-ASTERISK-ALFA, ALL "?" BY WC-QUESTION.
* Display debug field
     IF DEBUG-MODE
         DISPLAY SPACE, INTERNAL-FILENAME NO ADVANCING
     END-IF.
* Split PARAMETER4 into the different userid parts
     UNSTRING PARAMETER4 DELIMITED ",", OR SPACE INTO L-GROUP, L-USER.
* Check if group equals "*", in that case move "G" to WKLD-USERID-FLAG.
* The table WKLD-USERID-FLAG is used to represent the fact that group and/or
* user might be anything ("*"):
*    if the value is " " ----------------> group and user are defined
*    if the value is "G" ----------------> only group is defined
*    if the value is "U" ----------------> only user is defined
*    if the value is WC-ASTERISK-ALFA ---> group and user can be anything
     IF L-GROUP = "  *"
         MOVE WC-ASTERISK-ALFA TO WKLD-USERID-FLAG (WKLD-INDEX)
*        Display debug field
         IF DEBUG-MODE
             DISPLAY "    -1" NO ADVANCING
         END-IF
     ELSE
*        Check for a valid group number
         PERFORM 2166-GROUP
     END-IF.
     IF L-USER = "  *"
*        Display debug field
         IF DEBUG-MODE
             DISPLAY "    -1"
         END-IF
     ELSE
*        Check for a valid user number
         PERFORM 2168-USER
     END-IF.
*----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 2161-NEW-TITLE.
*    Insert the new TITLE-NUMBER
     ADD 1 TO TITLE-MAX.
     IF TITLE-MAX > TITLE-CEILING
*        This should never occur !
         STRING COMPLETION-54    DELIMITED SIZE
                " (TITLE-TABLE)" DELIMITED SIZE
                INTO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
         MOVE 1 TO ABEND-REQUIRED-FLAG
         PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
     END-IF.
     SET TITLE-INDEX TO TITLE-MAX.
     MOVE WKLD-NUMBER (WKLD-INDEX) TO
         TITLE-NUMBER OF TITLE-TABLE (TITLE-INDEX).
     MOVE SPACE TO TITLE-TYPE (TITLE-INDEX).
*----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 2162-SYSTEM.
*Start of Change-Validation Check for \ in Node name
      IF L-SYSTEM (1:1) NOT EQUAL "\"
          PERFORM 2300-INVALID-NODE-NAME
      END-IF
*End of Change-Validation Check for \ in Node name
      IF L-SYSTEM = SPACES OR L-SYSTEM NOT NODE-NAME
          PERFORM 2300-INVALID-NODE-NAME
      END-IF.
*     Check if system name exists
      SET SYSTEM-INDEX TO 1.
      SEARCH SYSTEM-TABLE
*         If name is not defined, no processes will fit into this
*           category; so let's just move a ZERO into WKLD-SYSTEM
          END MOVE ZERO TO WKLD-SYSTEM (WKLD-INDEX)
          WHEN SYSTEM-NAME OF SYSTEM-TABLE (SYSTEM-INDEX) = L-SYSTEM
              SET WKLD-SYSTEM (WKLD-INDEX) TO SYSTEM-INDEX
      END-SEARCH.
*----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 2163-CPU.
     IF L-CPU = SPACES
         PERFORM 2310-INVALID-CPU-NUMBER
     END-IF.
     INSPECT L-CPU REPLACING LEADING SPACE BY ZERO.
     MOVE L-CPU TO SCRATCH-99.
     IF SCRATCH-99 NOT NUMERIC
         PERFORM 2310-INVALID-CPU-NUMBER
     END-IF.
     IF SCRATCH-99 > 15
         PERFORM 2310-INVALID-CPU-NUMBER
     END-IF.
*    Store WKLD-CPU
     MOVE SCRATCH-99 TO WKLD-CPU (WKLD-INDEX).
*----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 2164-PIN.
     IF L-PIN = SPACES
         PERFORM 2320-INVALID-PIN-NUMBER
     END-IF.
     INSPECT L-PIN REPLACING LEADING SPACE BY ZERO.
     MOVE L-PIN TO SCRATCH-99999.
*Start of Change-Validation Check for PIN;should be numeric between 0 to 255
*    IF SCRATCH-99999 NOT NUMERIC
     IF SCRATCH-99999 NOT NUMERIC OR (SCRATCH-99999 < 00000 OR SCRATCH-99999 > 00255)
*End of Change-Validation Check for PIN;should be numeric between 0 to 255
         PERFORM 2320-INVALID-PIN-NUMBER
     END-IF.
*    Store WKLD-PIN
     MOVE SCRATCH-99999 TO WKLD-PIN (WKLD-INDEX).
*----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 2166-GROUP.
     IF L-GROUP = SPACES
         PERFORM 2330-INVALID-GROUP
     END-IF.
     INSPECT L-GROUP REPLACING LEADING SPACE BY ZERO.
     MOVE L-GROUP TO SCRATCH-999.
     IF SCRATCH-999 NOT NUMERIC
         PERFORM 2330-INVALID-GROUP
     END-IF.
     IF SCRATCH-999 > 255
         PERFORM 2330-INVALID-GROUP
     END-IF.
     MOVE GROUP-DEFINED TO WKLD-USERID-FLAG (WKLD-INDEX).
*    Store WKLD-GROUP
     MOVE SCRATCH-999 TO SCRATCH-NATIVE2.
     MOVE SCRATCH-X TO WKLD-GROUP (WKLD-INDEX).
*    Display debug field
     IF DEBUG-MODE
         DISPLAY SPACE, SCRATCH-NATIVE2 NO ADVANCING
     END-IF.
*----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 2168-USER.
     IF L-USER = SPACES
         PERFORM 2340-INVALID-USER
     END-IF.
     INSPECT L-USER REPLACING LEADING SPACE BY ZERO.
     MOVE L-USER TO SCRATCH-999.
     IF SCRATCH-999 NOT NUMERIC
         PERFORM 2340-INVALID-USER
     END-IF.
     IF SCRATCH-999 > 255
         PERFORM 2340-INVALID-USER
     END-IF.
*    Store WKLD-USER
     MOVE SCRATCH-999 TO SCRATCH-NATIVE2.
     MOVE SCRATCH-X TO WKLD-USER (WKLD-INDEX).
*    Check contents of WKLD-USERID-FLAG
     IF WKLD-USERID-FLAG (WKLD-INDEX) = WC-ASTERISK-ALFA
*        In this case the group was not defined
         MOVE USER-DEFINED TO WKLD-USERID-FLAG (WKLD-INDEX)
     ELSE
*        In this case the group was also defined
         MOVE SPACE TO WKLD-USERID-FLAG (WKLD-INDEX)
     END-IF.
*    Display debug field
     IF DEBUG-MODE
         DISPLAY SPACE, SCRATCH-NATIVE2
     END-IF.
*----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 2170-TITLE-INPUT.
* Keyword TITLE detected
     SET TITLE-DETECTED TO TRUE.
* Obtain category number
     MOVE KEYWORD (6:2) TO SCRATCH-99.
     IF SCRATCH-99 NOT NUMERIC
         STRING COMPLETION-39 DELIMITED SIZE
                SPACE         DELIMITED SIZE
                KEYWORD (6:2) DELIMITED SIZE
                INTO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
         PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
     END-IF.
* Make sure that TITLE-NUMBER is already there
     MOVE SCRATCH-99 TO SCRATCH-NATIVE2.
     SET TITLE-INDEX TO 1.
     SEARCH TITLE-TABLE
         END
             PERFORM
                 STRING COMPLETION-40 DELIMITED SIZE
                        SPACE         DELIMITED SIZE
                        KEYWORD (6:2) DELIMITED SIZE
                        INTO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
                 PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
             END-PERFORM
         WHEN TITLE-NUMBER OF TITLE-TABLE (TITLE-INDEX) = SCRATCH-X
             NEXT SENTENCE
     END-SEARCH.
* Check that no two TITLE entries with the same number exist
     IF TITLE-TYPE (TITLE-INDEX) NOT = SPACE
         STRING COMPLETION-41 DELIMITED SIZE
                SPACE         DELIMITED SIZE
                KEYWORD (6:2) DELIMITED SIZE
                INTO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
         PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
     END-IF.
* Split PARAMETER1 into category type and name
     MOVE SPACES TO L-TITLE.
*Change-Validation check-modified parameter L-TITILE to TEMP-L-TITLE
     UNSTRING PARAMETER1 DELIMITED "," , OR SPACE
         INTO TITLE-TYPE (TITLE-INDEX), TEMP-L-TITLE.
* Verify category type
     IF NOT TITLE-TYPE (TITLE-INDEX) VALID-CATEGORY-TYPES
         STRING COMPLETION-15 DELIMITED SIZE
                SPACE         DELIMITED SIZE
                KEYWORD (6:2) DELIMITED SIZE
                INTO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
         PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
     END-IF.
* Check for a valid category name
*Start of change-Validation added for TITLE entry
     IF TEMP-L-TITLE (9:1) NOT EQUAL SPACES
         STRING COMPLETION-16 DELIMITED SIZE
                         SPACE         DELIMITED SIZE
                         KEYWORD (6:2) DELIMITED SIZE
                         INTO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
         PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
     END-IF
     MOVE TEMP-L-TITLE TO L-TITLE
*End of change-Validation added for TITLE entry
     IF L-TITLE = SPACES     OR
        L-TITLE (1:1) = "!"  OR
        L-TITLE = "_OTHER"   OR
        L-TITLE = "_ERROR"
         STRING COMPLETION-16 DELIMITED SIZE
                SPACE         DELIMITED SIZE
                KEYWORD (6:2) DELIMITED SIZE
                INTO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
         PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
     END-IF.
* Check that the same category name is not already used
     SET TITLE-INDEX-2 TO 1.
     SEARCH TITLE-TABLE VARYING TITLE-INDEX-2
         WHEN TITLE-NAME (TITLE-INDEX-2) = L-TITLE
             STRING COMPLETION-17 DELIMITED SIZE
                    SPACE         DELIMITED SIZE
                    KEYWORD (6:2) DELIMITED SIZE
                    INTO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
             PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
     END-SEARCH.
* Store TITLE-NAME
     MOVE L-TITLE TO TITLE-NAME (TITLE-INDEX).
* Display debug fields
     IF DEBUG-MODE DISPLAY ">TITLE", KEYWORD (6:2), ": ",
         TITLE-TYPE (TITLE-INDEX), SPACE
         TITLE-NAME (TITLE-INDEX)
     END-IF.
*----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 2180-TXN-INPUT.
* Keyword TXN detected
* Split PARAMETER1 in transaction type and name
     MOVE SPACES TO TXN-LINE.
     UNSTRING PARAMETER1 DELIMITED ",", OR SPACE
         INTO L-TXN-TYPE, L-TXN-NAME.
* Verify transaction type
     IF NOT L-TXN-TYPE VALID-TRANSACTION-TYPES
         STRING COMPLETION-69 DELIMITED SIZE
                SPACE         DELIMITED SIZE
                L-TXN-TYPE    DELIMITED SIZE
                INTO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
         PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
     END-IF.
* Check for valid transaction name
     IF L-TXN-NAME = SPACES OR L-TXN-NAME (1:1) = "!"
         MOVE COMPLETION-19 TO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
         PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
     END-IF.
* Check for duplicates
     SET TXN-INDEX TO 1.
     SEARCH TXN-TABLE
         WHEN TXN-NAME (TXN-INDEX) = L-TXN-NAME
             STRING COMPLETION-20 DELIMITED SIZE
                    SPACE         DELIMITED SIZE
                    L-TXN-NAME    DELIMITED SIZE
                    INTO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
             PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
     END-SEARCH.
     ADD 1 TO TXN-MAX.
* The maximum number of user-defined transactions is TXN-CEILING
     IF TXN-MAX > TXN-CEILING
         MOVE COMPLETION-59 TO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
         PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
     END-IF.
* Store TXN-NAME
     SET TXN-INDEX TO TXN-MAX.
     MOVE L-TXN-TYPE TO TXN-TYPE (TXN-INDEX).
     MOVE L-TXN-NAME TO TXN-NAME (TXN-INDEX).
* Display debug field
     IF DEBUG-MODE
         DISPLAY ">TXN: ", TXN-TYPE (TXN-INDEX), SPACE, TXN-NAME (TXN-INDEX)
     END-IF.
*----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 2190-REPORT-INPUT.
* Keyword REPORT detected
* Check for duplicates
     IF AUDIT-REPORT-YES
         MOVE COMPLETION-43 TO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
         PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
     END-IF.
* Check for valid report location
     IF PARAMETER1 = SPACES OR PARAMETER1 (1:1) = "!"
         MOVE COMPLETION-44 TO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
         PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
     END-IF.
* Store REPORT-LOCATION
     MOVE PARAMETER1 TO REPORT-LOCATION.
     SET AUDIT-REPORT-YES TO TRUE.
* Display debug field
     IF DEBUG-MODE
         DISPLAY ">REPORT: ", REPORT-LOCATION
     END-IF.
*----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 2200-CONVERTTO-INPUT.
* Keyword CONVERTTO detected
* Check for duplicates
     IF CONVERTTO-PRESENT
         MOVE COMPLETION-74 TO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
         PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
     END-IF.
* Soln 10-000602-8415. A check to ensure that at least one parameter is passed
     IF PARAMETER1 = SPACES
           MOVE COMPLETION-75 TO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
           PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
     END-IF
* Obtain CPU power value
     SET CPU-TYPE-POWER-INDEX TO 1.
     SEARCH CPU-TYPE-POWER-TABLE
         END
*            Invalid CPU type entered
             PERFORM
                 MOVE COMPLETION-75 TO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
                 PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
             END-PERFORM
         WHEN CPU-TYPE-ALFA (CPU-TYPE-POWER-INDEX) = PARAMETER1
             NEXT SENTENCE
     END-SEARCH.
* Store the CONVERTTO values of CPU-type, CPU-subtype and OS-version in
* temporary variables. Validate the second parameter of CONVERTTO.
* Changes start here - Soln 10-000602-8415.
     MOVE PARAMETER1 TO CONVERTTO-CPU-NAME.
     MOVE CPU-TYPE-NUMBER OF CPU-TYPE-SUBTYPE (CPU-TYPE-POWER-INDEX)
        TO TEMP-CPU-TYPE.
     MOVE CPU-SUBTYPE-NUMBER OF CPU-TYPE-SUBTYPE (CPU-TYPE-POWER-INDEX)
        TO TEMP-CPU-SUBTYPE.
     MOVE SPACES TO TEMP-OS-VERSION-LETTER.
     IF PARAMETER2 (1:3) NOT = SPACES
        MOVE PARAMETER2 (1:1) TO TEMP-OS-VERSION-LETTER
* J-Series Blades Change: "J" "j" Guardian-Type added.
* MeasTCM Yosemite Change: "H" "h" Guardian-Type added.
*        IF TEMP-OS-VERSION-LETTER NOT = "D" AND "d" AND "g" AND "G" AND "c" AND "C"
*                                        AND "H" AND "h" AND "J" AND "j"
        IF TEMP-OS-VERSION-LETTER NOT = "g" AND "G"
                                        AND "H" AND "h" AND "J" AND "j"
           PERFORM 8999-OS-VERSION-ERROR
        END-IF
        MOVE PARAMETER2 (2:2) TO TEMP-OS-VERSION-NUMBER
        IF TEMP-OS-VERSION-NUMBER NOT = SPACES
          IF PARAMETER2 (2:1) NOT NUMERIC AND PARAMETER2 (2:1) NOT = "X" AND "x"
             PERFORM 8999-OS-VERSION-ERROR
          END-IF
          IF PARAMETER2 (3:1) NOT NUMERIC AND PARAMETER2 (3:1) NOT = "X" AND "x"
             PERFORM 8999-OS-VERSION-ERROR
          END-IF
        END-IF
     END-IF.
* Changes end here - Soln 10-000602-8415.
     SET CPU-TYPE-POWER-CONVERTTO TO CPU-TYPE-POWER-INDEX.
     SET CONVERTTO-PRESENT        TO TRUE.
* Check for optional 2nd parameter of D or G or H -convert to D or G or H series
* Soln 10-000602-8415. The IF condition below for Debug mode is modified. Only
* 1st character of parameter2 is compared with "D/d/G/g/H/h", since parameter2 can
* also contain the factor 'u' of CONVERTTO. DISPLAY statements are now executed
* when Debug mode is off and parameter2 contains only a single character.
*     IF PARAMETER2 = "d" OR "D" OR "g" OR "G"
* J-Series Blades Change: "J" "j" Guardian-Type added.
* IF PARAMETER2 (1:1) = "d" OR "D" OR "g" OR "G" OR "h" OR "H" OR "j" OR "J"
  IF PARAMETER2 (1:1) = "g" OR "G" OR "h" OR "H" OR "j" OR "J"
         IF DEBUG-MODE
*            MOVE "D" TO CONVERT-GUARDIAN-VERSION
            MOVE "G" TO CONVERT-GUARDIAN-VERSION
         ELSE
             IF PARAMETER2 (2:2) = SPACES
*               DISPLAY ">D,G,H J Option on CONVERTTO only valid in DEBUG mode."
               DISPLAY ">G,H J Option on CONVERTTO only valid in DEBUG mode."
               DISPLAY ">    Option ignored."
         END-IF
      END-IF.
* Display debug fields
     IF DEBUG-MODE
         DISPLAY
           ">CONVERTTO: (CICS,RICS) "
           CPU-TYPE-ALFA (CPU-TYPE-POWER-CONVERTTO)
           SPACE
*           CPU-POWER-VALUE-CNN (CPU-TYPE-POWER-CONVERTTO)
*           SPACE
*           CPU-POWER-VALUE-DNN (CPU-TYPE-POWER-CONVERTTO)
           CPU-POWER-VALUE-GNN (CPU-TYPE-POWER-CONVERTTO)
*         IF PARAMETER2 = "d" OR "D" or "g" OR "G" OR "h" OR "H" OR "j" OR "J"
          IF PARAMETER2 = "g" OR "G" OR "h" OR "H" OR "j" OR "J"
               DISPLAY ">CONVERTTO: ", PARAMETER2, " Option Detected"
           END-IF
     END-IF.
*----------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Soln 10-020415-8203 : start
  2240-DISKCONVERTTO-INPUT.
* Keyword DISKCONVERTTO detected
* Check for duplicates
     IF DISKCONVERTTO-PRESENT
         MOVE COMPLETION-93 TO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
         PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
     END-IF.
* Check to ensure that at least one parameter is passed
     IF PARAMETER1 = SPACES
           MOVE COMPLETION-94 TO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
           PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
     END-IF
* Obtain DISK values
     SET DISK-SUBTYPE-INDEX TO 1.
     SEARCH DISK-TYPE-POWER-TABLE
         END
*            Invalid DISK type entered
             PERFORM
                 MOVE COMPLETION-94 TO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
                 PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
             END-PERFORM
         WHEN DISK-TYPE-ALFA (DISK-SUBTYPE-INDEX) = PARAMETER1 AND DISK-SUBTYPE-NUMBER (DISK-SUBTYPE-INDEX) NOT = 52
             NEXT SENTENCE
     END-SEARCH.
     MOVE PARAMETER1 TO DISKTO-DISK-MODEL-NAME.
     SET DISK-TYPE-POWER-CONVERTTO TO DISK-SUBTYPE-INDEX.
* Check if DISKCONVERTTO contains SAS disk
        If DISK-SUBTYPE-NUMBER (DISK-TYPE-POWER-CONVERTTO)  = 51
           MOVE 1 TO SASDISK-FLAG
* Check for WCE status
           IF PARAMETER2 = SPACES OR "OFF" OR "off"
                MOVE "OFF" TO DISKTO-DISK-WCE
           ELSE IF PARAMETER2 = "ON" OR "on"
                MOVE "ON" TO DISKTO-DISK-WCE
           ELSE
                MOVE COMPLETION-109 TO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
                PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
           END-IF
        ELSE
* If DISKCONVERTTO contains non-SAS disk, check for WCE status
           IF PARAMETER2 = SPACES OR "NA" OR "na"
                MOVE "NA" TO DISKTO-DISK-WCE
           ELSE
                MOVE COMPLETION-94 TO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
                PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
           END-IF
        END-IF
     SET DISKCONVERTTO-PRESENT        TO TRUE.
* Display debug fields
     IF DEBUG-MODE
         DISPLAY
           ">DISKCONVERTTO: (Model, Controller, WCE Status) "
           DISK-TYPE-ALFA (DISK-TYPE-POWER-CONVERTTO)
           SPACE
           DISK-CONTROLLER (DISK-TYPE-POWER-CONVERTTO)
           SPACE
           DISKTO-DISK-WCE
     END-IF.
* Soln 10-020415-8203 : end
*----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 2210-INVALID-KEYWORD.
* Invalid keyword detected
     STRING COMPLETION-21 DELIMITED SIZE
            SPACE         DELIMITED SIZE
            KEYWORD       DELIMITED SIZE
            INTO COMPLETION-MESSAGE.
     PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION.
*----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 2220-CPUFACTOR-INPUT.
* Keyword CPUFACTOR detected
* Check Guardian type
     MOVE PARAMETER2 TO GUARDIAN-TYPE.
     IF NOT VALID-GUARDIAN-TYPE
*        If not a valid  G H or J check if alpha
         IF GUARDIAN-TYPE ALPHABETIC
            MOVE COMPLETION-85 TO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
            PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
         ELSE
*           Assume no guardian type provided so default to G
            MOVE PARAMETER4 TO PARAMETER5
            MOVE PARAMETER3 TO PARAMETER4
            MOVE PARAMETER2 TO PARAMETER3
*            MOVE "D" TO GUARDIAN-TYPE
            MOVE "G" TO GUARDIAN-TYPE
         END-IF
     ELSE
         IF GUARDIAN-TYPE = "j" OR "J"
            MOVE 1 TO JCPU-FLAG
            MOVE "G" TO GUARDIAN-TYPE
         ELSE
            MOVE "G" TO GUARDIAN-TYPE
         END-IF
     END-IF.
* Isolate power value
     UNSTRING PARAMETER3 DELIMITED ALL SPACE INTO CPUPOWER-ENTERED.
* Soln 10-020717-0465:start
* Check for format xxxx.yy
     IF CPUPOWER-ENTERED (1:1) NOT NUMERIC OR
        CPUPOWER-ENTERED (2:1) NOT NUMERIC OR
        CPUPOWER-ENTERED (3:1) NOT NUMERIC OR
        CPUPOWER-ENTERED (4:1) NOT NUMERIC OR
        CPUPOWER-ENTERED (5:1) NOT = "."   OR
        CPUPOWER-ENTERED (6:1) NOT NUMERIC OR
        CPUPOWER-ENTERED (7:1) NOT NUMERIC
* Soln 10-020717-0465:end
*        Invalid CPU power value entered
         MOVE COMPLETION-78 TO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
         PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
     END-IF.
* Obtain index into CPU-TYPE-POWER-TABLE and check if CPU exist
     SET CPU-TYPE-POWER-INDEX TO 1.
     SEARCH CPU-TYPE-POWER-TABLE
         END
*            Invalid CPU type entered
*            GAG IPM AAK.   Check if ok to add new type.
             PERFORM 2225-ADD-NEW-CPU-TYPE
         WHEN CPU-TYPE-ALFA (CPU-TYPE-POWER-INDEX) = PARAMETER1
             NEXT SENTENCE
     END-SEARCH.
* Check if CPU power entered > 0
     IF CPUPOWER-ENTERED-RED <= ZERO
         MOVE COMPLETION-78 TO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
         PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
     END-IF.
         MOVE CPUPOWER-ENTERED-RED
              TO CPU-POWER-VALUE-GNN (CPU-TYPE-POWER-INDEX).
* Display debug fields
     IF DEBUG-MODE
         DISPLAY
           ">CPUPOWER (CICS,RISC): "
           CPU-TYPE-ALFA (CPU-TYPE-POWER-INDEX)
           SPACE
*           CPU-POWER-VALUE-CNN (CPU-TYPE-POWER-INDEX)
*           SPACE
*           CPU-POWER-VALUE-DNN (CPU-TYPE-POWER-INDEX)
           CPU-POWER-VALUE-GNN (CPU-TYPE-POWER-INDEX)
     END-IF.
*----------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Soln 10-020415-8203 : start
  2250-DISKFACTOR-INPUT.
* Keyword DISKFACTOR detected
* Obtain index into DISK-TYPE-POWER-TABLE
     SET DISK-SUBTYPE-INDEX TO 1.
     SEARCH DISK-TYPE-POWER-TABLE
         END
*            Invalid DISK type entered
*            Check if ok to add new type.
             PERFORM 2255-ADD-NEW-DISK-TYPE
         WHEN DISK-TYPE-ALFA (DISK-SUBTYPE-INDEX) = PARAMETER1
             NEXT SENTENCE
