*----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 2400-MEASURE-TABLE-SCAN.
      SET MEASURE-INDEX TO TEMP-INDEX.
      MOVE TEMP-INDEX TO MEAS-INDEX.
      MOVE 1 TO RUN-MEAS-MSG-INDX.
      MOVE "Y" TO MEASURE-VALID-FILE(MEASURE-INDEX).
      MOVE MEASURE-START OF MEASURE-TABLE(MEASURE-INDEX) TO TEMP-TIMESTAMP.
      ENTER TAL "INTERPRETTIMESTAMP" USING
                TEMP-TIMESTAMP, DATE-N-TIME GIVING RESULT-4.
      MOVE CORR DATE-N-TIME TO CSVTIME.
      MOVE CSVTIME          TO TEMP-FROM-TIME OF TEMP-LINE-2.
* Set the stop time if CSVHI is available.
      IF (MEASURE-STOP(MEASURE-INDEX)) = -1
         IF CSVHI ZERO
            MOVE INFO-15 TO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
                            RUN-MEAS-ADV(TEMP-INDEX, RUN-MEAS-MSG-INDX)
            MOVE INFO-19 TO RUN-MEAS-FILE-ADV
            SET C-EXIT-PROGRAM TO TRUE
            PERFORM 2490-PRE-EXIT
         ELSE
            MOVE CSVHI TO MEASURE-STOP(MEASURE-INDEX)
            MOVE INFO-20 TO RUN-MEAS-ADV(TEMP-INDEX, RUN-MEAS-MSG-INDX)
            ADD 1 TO RUN-MEAS-MSG-INDX
            PERFORM 2420-SCAN-PART-2
         END-IF
      ELSE
         PERFORM 2420-SCAN-PART-2
      END-IF.
*----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 2420-SCAN-PART-2.
      MOVE MEASURE-STOP(MEASURE-INDEX) TO TEMP-TIMESTAMP.
      ENTER TAL "INTERPRETTIMESTAMP" USING
                TEMP-TIMESTAMP, DATE-N-TIME GIVING RESULT-4.
      MOVE CORR DATE-N-TIME TO CSVTIME.
      MOVE CSVTIME          TO TEMP-TO-TIME OF TEMP-LINE-2.
* Check if this measure file lies within user specified time window
      IF CSVHI NOT ZERO
         IF MEASURE-START OF MEASURE-TABLE(MEASURE-INDEX) > CSVHI
            MOVE INFO-21 TO RUN-MEAS-ADV(TEMP-INDEX, RUN-MEAS-MSG-INDX)
            ADD 1 TO RUN-MEAS-MSG-INDX
            MOVE INFO-22 TO RUN-MEAS-ADV(TEMP-INDEX, RUN-MEAS-MSG-INDX)
            ADD 1 TO RUN-MEAS-MSG-INDX
            MOVE "N" TO MEASURE-VALID-FILE(MEASURE-INDEX)
         END-IF
      END-IF.
      IF CSVLO NOT ZERO
         IF MEASURE-STOP(MEASURE-INDEX) < CSVLO
            MOVE INFO-21 TO RUN-MEAS-ADV(TEMP-INDEX, RUN-MEAS-MSG-INDX)
            ADD 1 TO RUN-MEAS-MSG-INDX
            MOVE INFO-22 TO RUN-MEAS-ADV(TEMP-INDEX, RUN-MEAS-MSG-INDX)
            ADD 1 TO RUN-MEAS-MSG-INDX
            MOVE "N" TO MEASURE-VALID-FILE(MEASURE-INDEX)
         END-IF
      END-IF.
      IF MEASURE-VALID-FILE(MEASURE-INDEX) = "Y"
         ADD 1 TO NUM-VALID-FILES
      END-IF.
* Check for overlap. Check if the start time of current file is less than
* stop time of previous valid file.
     IF (NUM-VALID-FILES > 1)
        IF (MEASURE-VALID-FILE(MEASURE-INDEX) = "Y")
          IF (MEASURE-START OF MEASURE-TABLE(MEASURE-INDEX) >
                     PREVIOUS-STOP-TIME)
            MOVE INFO-16 TO RUN-MEAS-ADV(TEMP-INDEX, RUN-MEAS-MSG-INDX)
            ADD 1 TO RUN-MEAS-MSG-INDX
          END-IF
        END-IF
     END-IF.
* Set the previous-stop-time to stop time of current file.
     MOVE MEASURE-STOP(MEASURE-INDEX) TO PREVIOUS-STOP-TIME.
* Set the interval if it is -1 for this file
* Divide the (stop - start) by 1000000 and multiply by 1000000 to give the
* interval rounded. The start and stop times calculated will not go out of
* range.
    IF (MEASURE-INT(MEASURE-INDEX) = -1)
       COMPUTE MEASURE-INT(MEASURE-INDEX) =
              (MEASURE-STOP(MEASURE-INDEX) -
              MEASURE-START OF MEASURE-TABLE(MEASURE-INDEX)) / 1000000
       COMPUTE MEASURE-INT(MEASURE-INDEX) =
                   MEASURE-INT(MEASURE-INDEX) * 1000000
       MOVE INFO-17 TO RUN-MEAS-ADV(TEMP-INDEX, RUN-MEAS-MSG-INDX)
       ADD 1 TO RUN-MEAS-MSG-INDX
    END-IF.
    DIVIDE MEASURE-INT(MEASURE-INDEX) BY 1000000 GIVING TEMP-COLL-INT.
* Compute LCM of intervals
   IF MEASURE-VALID-FILE(MEASURE-INDEX) = "N"
      PERFORM 2490-PRE-EXIT
   ELSE
*     If the index = 1, set lcm = interval
      IF (MEASURE-INDEX = 1)  OR (LCM = 0)
          MOVE  MEASURE-INT(MEASURE-INDEX) TO LCM
          PERFORM 2490-PRE-EXIT
      ELSE
*         Get GCD of lcm and interval of current element.
          MOVE MEASURE-INT(MEASURE-INDEX) TO NUMERATOR
          IF (NUMERATOR = LCM) OR (LCM < 0)
              PERFORM 2490-PRE-EXIT
          ELSE
              PERFORM 2480-SCAN-PART-3
          END-IF
       END-IF
   END-IF.
*----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 2480-SCAN-PART-3.
* Since the interval is not the same as the lcm of previous values,
* compute the gcd of the lcm and the interval and use this to find lcm.
   MOVE LCM TO DENOMINATOR.
* If numerator < denominator, switch values so that numerator > denominator.
   IF (NUMERATOR < DENOMINATOR)
      MOVE NUMERATOR TO TEMP-STORE
      MOVE DENOMINATOR       TO NUMERATOR
      MOVE TEMP-STORE TO DENOMINATOR
   END-IF.
* Find the GCD of interval and denominator. Divide interval by denominator.
* If rem = 0 denominator is the gcd. If rem not zero, move denominator to
* numerator, rem to denominator and repeat until rem = 0.
   MOVE "N" TO EXIT-GCD.
   PERFORM UNTIL C-EXIT-GCD
      DIVIDE NUMERATOR BY DENOMINATOR GIVING QUOTIENT REMAINDER REM
      IF REM ZERO
         MOVE DENOMINATOR TO GCD
         SET C-EXIT-GCD TO TRUE
      ELSE
         MOVE DENOMINATOR TO NUMERATOR
         MOVE REM TO DENOMINATOR
      END-IF
   END-PERFORM.
* Find the factor by which the lcm and interval are divisible by gcd
   COMPUTE FACTOR-1 = MEASURE-INT(MEASURE-INDEX) / GCD.
   COMPUTE FACTOR-2 = LCM / GCD.
* The lcm = product of the two factors and the gcd.
   COMPUTE LCM = FACTOR-1 * FACTOR-2 * GCD
   ON SIZE ERROR
      MOVE -1 TO LCM
   END-COMPUTE.
   PERFORM 2490-PRE-EXIT.
*----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 2490-PRE-EXIT.
      SET SYSTEM-INDEX TO MEASURE-SYSTEM-NUMBER(MEASURE-INDEX).
      MOVE SPACES TO MEAS-SYS-NAME.
      MOVE SYSTEM-NAME OF SYSTEM-TABLE(SYSTEM-INDEX) TO MEAS-SYS-NAME.
      MOVE SPACES TO INTERNAL-FILENAME.
      MOVE MEASURE-DATAFILE(MEASURE-INDEX) TO INTERNAL-FILENAME.
      STRING PART1 DELIMITED BY SPACES,
             "."   DELIMITED BY SIZE,
             PART2 DELIMITED BY SPACES,
             "."   DELIMITED BY SIZE,
             PART3 DELIMITED BY SIZE
      INTO MEAS-FILE-NAME.
      MOVE TEMP-LINE-1 TO RUN-MEAS-LINE-1(TEMP-INDEX).
      MOVE TEMP-LINE-2 TO RUN-MEAS-LINE-2(TEMP-INDEX).
*----------------------------------------------------------------------------
*----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 3000-CORE-PROCESSING.
* Loop through the process of reading the measure data files, generating the
* csv data file for all files possible.
      PERFORM 3000-CORE-PROCESSING-MAIN
           VARYING FILE-NUM FROM 1 BY 1
           UNTIL FILE-NUM > NUM-CSVS-ACTUAL.
* Close all measure data files
      PERFORM 5000-CLOSE-MEASDATA.
*----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 3000-CORE-PROCESSING-MAIN.
   MOVE FILE-NUM TO CSVDATA(POS:3).
   MOVE CSVDATA  TO CSV-FILE-NAME.
   MOVE CSV-FILE-NAME TO P-CSV-FILE.
*  Set the time window for the csvdata file and the measure data files.
   IF MEAS-START ZERO
      MOVE EARLIEST-START-TIME TO MEAS-START
   ELSE
      MOVE MEAS-STOP TO MEAS-START
   END-IF.
   IF (FILE-NUM = NUM-CSVS-ACTUAL) OR (LCM < 0)
      MOVE LATEST-STOP-TIME TO MEAS-STOP
   ELSE
      COMPUTE MEAS-STOP = MEAS-START + (LCM * NUM-OF-LCMS)
   END-IF.
* Set the low and high times in the csv record
   ENTER TAL "INTERPRETTIMESTAMP" USING MEAS-START, DATE-N-TIME
                                  GIVING RESULT-4.
   MOVE CORR DATE-N-TIME TO CSVTIME.
   MOVE CORR CSVTIME     TO I04.
   MOVE CORR CSVTIME     TO I05.
   MOVE      CSVTIME     TO FROM-WINDOW
                            TEMP-FROM-TIME OF CSV-TEMP-2.
   ENTER TAL "INTERPRETTIMESTAMP" USING MEAS-STOP, DATE-N-TIME
                                  GIVING RESULT-4.
   MOVE CORR DATE-N-TIME TO CSVTIME.
   MOVE CORR CSVTIME     TO I06.
   MOVE CORR CSVTIME     TO I07.
   MOVE      CSVTIME     TO TO-WINDOW
                            TEMP-TO-TIME OF CSV-TEMP-2.
* Business as usual for this csv file.
   DISPLAY INFO-27, SPACE, CSVDATA.
   PERFORM 3000-CORE-PROCESSING-CONT.
* Initialize all areas required for the next csv data file
   PERFORM VARYING VOLUME-INDEX FROM 1 BY 1
         UNTIL VOLUME-INDEX > VOLUME-MAX
      INITIALIZE VOLUME-SORT-MOVE(VOLUME-INDEX)
          REPLACING NUMERIC DATA BY ZERO
               ALPHANUMERIC DATA BY SPACES
      MOVE ZERO TO NO-OF-FILES(VOLUME-INDEX)
                   NO-OF-VOLUME-RECS(VOLUME-INDEX)
                   DISC-READ-COST(VOLUME-INDEX)
                   DISC-WRITE-COST(VOLUME-INDEX)
                   DISC-TO-DOPN-READ-RATIO(VOLUME-INDEX)
                   DISC-TO-DOPN-WRITE-RATIO(VOLUME-INDEX)
   END-PERFORM.
   PERFORM VARYING PROCESS-INDEX FROM 1 BY 1
         UNTIL PROCESS-INDEX > PROCESS-MAX
      INITIALIZE PROCESS-SORT-KEY OF PROCESS-TABLE(PROCESS-INDEX)
          REPLACING NUMERIC DATA BY ZERO
               ALPHANUMERIC DATA BY SPACES
      MOVE ZERO TO PROCESS-TO(PROCESS-INDEX)
                   PROCESS-UNIQUE(PROCESS-INDEX)
      MOVE SPACES TO PROCESS-WKLD-NUMBER(PROCESS-INDEX)
   END-PERFORM.
   PERFORM VARYING TITLE-INDEX FROM 1 BY 1
         UNTIL TITLE-INDEX > TITLE-MAX
       INITIALIZE CSV-W-BINARY(TITLE-INDEX)
              REPLACING NUMERIC DATA BY ZERO
                   ALPHANUMERIC DATA BY SPACES
   END-PERFORM.
   MOVE ZERO TO D01
                D02
                VOLUME-MAX
                F02
                F03 OF CSV-F-COMP
                C02 OF CSV-C-BINARY
                C03 OF CSV-C-BINARY
                F03 OF CSV-F-DATA
                PROCESS-MAX
                CPU-MAX
                UNIQUE-COUNTER
*               GAG.  IPM AAI.
                MEASURE-FILE-OVERFLOW
                NUMBER-LINKED-DISCOPENS
                NUMBER-UNLINKED-DISCOPENS
                NUMBER-UNLINKED-DISCOPENS-R.
   MOVE 32767 TO DFVERSION-SAVE.
*----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 3000-CORE-PROCESSING-CONT.
* Obtain all disc information
     DISPLAY INFO-08.
     PERFORM 3201-SPDISKINFO
         VARYING MEASURE-INDEX FROM 1 BY 1
         UNTIL MEASURE-INDEX > MEASURE-MAX.
* Display debug fields
     IF DEBUG-MODE
         DISPLAY ">VOLUME-MAX: ", VOLUME-MAX
     END-IF.
* Fill in D01
* Soln 10-020415-8203 : start
* Soln 10-040510-5889 : start
* IF DISKCONVERTTO-PRESENT
*   COMPUTE
*        D01 ROUNDED = VOLUME-MAX + DISK-POWER-VALUE
*   END-COMPUTE
* ELSE
     MOVE VOLUME-MAX TO D01
* END-IF.
* Soln 10-040510-5889 : end
* Soln 10-020415-8203 : end
* Calculate number of drives. For each measure data file, for each vol.,
* there will be two records for unmirrorred vol. and more than that for
* mirrorred vol. The calculation of # of drives is then by storing  the
* number of occurrances of a volume across all the data files and the number
* of measure files it occurs in, checking if the number of occurrances is
* > the product of # of files * 4. If so, the volume is mirrorred.
* TPR # S930119 1403 14751.
     MOVE ZERO TO D02.
     PERFORM VARYING VOLUME-INDEX FROM 1 BY 1
           UNTIL VOLUME-INDEX > VOLUME-MAX
        IF NO-OF-VOLUME-RECS(VOLUME-INDEX) >
             (NO-OF-FILES(VOLUME-INDEX) * 4)
           ADD 2 TO D02
        ELSE
           ADD 1 TO D02
        END-IF
     END-PERFORM.
* Soln 10-020415-8203 : start
* Soln 10-040510-5889 : start
*   IF DISKCONVERTTO-PRESENT
*     COMPUTE
*          D02 ROUNDED = D02 + DISK-POWER-VALUE
*     END-COMPUTE
*   END-IF.
* Soln 10-040510-5889 : end
* Soln 10-020415-8203 : end
* Sort VOLUME-TABLE
     PERFORM 3240-VOLUME-TABLE-SORT.
* Obtain discopen totals for each volume
     MOVE ZERO TO FIRSTCALL.
     PERFORM 3500-READ-DISCOPEN-TOTALS VARYING MEASURE-INDEX
        FROM 1 BY 1 UNTIL MEASURE-INDEX > MEASURE-MAX.
* Calculate READ/WRITE cost and disc-to-discopen ratio for each volume
     PERFORM 3250-CALCULATE-READ-WRITE-COST.
* Obtain CPU and process information on a system by system basis; for each
* system go through the corresponding measurement data files. If audit report
* is selected, process information must be released to sort
     IF AUDIT-REPORT-YES
         MOVE ZERO TO LAST-RECORD-TEST
         SORT SORT-FILE ASCENDING SORT-WKLD-NAME
                        ASCENDING SORT-SYSTEM-NAME
                        ASCENDING SORT-PROGRAM-FILE-NAME
                        ASCENDING SORT-PROCESS-NAME
                        ASCENDING SORT-CPU-NUM
                        ASCENDING SORT-PIN-X
             INPUT  PROCEDURE 3010-CORE-PROCESSING-CONT
             OUTPUT PROCEDURE 4000-PRINT-REPORT
     ELSE
         PERFORM 3010-CORE-PROCESSING-CONT
     END-IF.
     PERFORM 6000-WRITE-CSV.
** Fill up the csv array for run summary
     MOVE CSV-TEMP-1 TO RUN-CSV-LINE-1(FILE-NUM).
     MOVE CSV-TEMP-2 TO RUN-CSV-LINE-2(FILE-NUM).
     MOVE CSV-TEMP-3 TO RUN-CSV-ADV(FILE-NUM).
     MOVE SPACES     TO CSV-TEMP-3.
*----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 3010-CORE-PROCESSING-CONT.
* Obtain information on a system by system basis
     MOVE "$*" TO FILE-NAME OF ALL-DISCOPENS (1:2).
     PERFORM 3020-SYSTEM-LOOP VARYING SYSTEM-INDEX FROM 1 BY 1
         UNTIL SYSTEM-INDEX > SYSTEM-MAX.
* Display debug fields
     IF DEBUG-MODE
         DISPLAY ">NUMBER-LINKED-DISCOPENS: ",
                   NUMBER-LINKED-DISCOPENS,
                 " NUMBER-UNLINKED-DISCOPENS: ",
                   NUMBER-UNLINKED-DISCOPENS,
*                  NUMBER-UNLINKED-DISCOPENS-R IS THE NUMBER OF DISCOPENS
*                  THAT WERE NOT LINKED BECAUSE THE OWNER PROCESSES WERE
*                  ON REMOTE SYSTEMS THAT WERE NOT MEASURED
                 " NUMBER-UNLINKED-DISCOPENS-R: ",
                   NUMBER-UNLINKED-DISCOPENS-R
     END-IF.
* Calculate percentage of discopens linked
     IF NOT (NUMBER-LINKED-DISCOPENS ZERO AND NUMBER-UNLINKED-DISCOPENS ZERO)
         COMPUTE PERCENT-LINKED = NUMBER-LINKED-DISCOPENS *
             100 / (NUMBER-LINKED-DISCOPENS + NUMBER-UNLINKED-DISCOPENS)
         MOVE PERCENT-LINKED TO PERCENTAGE-LINKED-DISCOPENS
         MOVE PERCENTAGE-LINKED-DISCOPENS TO CSV-LINK
         DISPLAY PERCENTAGE-LINKED-DISCOPENS, SPACE, INFO-13
         IF PERCENT-LINKED < 90
            DISPLAY INFO-18
            IF CSV-TEMP-3 = SPACES
              MOVE INFO-18 TO CSV-TEMP-3
            END-IF
         END-IF
     ELSE
*      GAG, IPM AAI.
       MOVE ZERO    TO CSV-LINK
       IF CSV-TEMP-3 = SPACES
         MOVE INFO-26 TO CSV-TEMP-3
       END-IF
       DISPLAY INFO-26
     END-IF.
     IF AUDIT-REPORT-YES
         DISPLAY INFO-11
     END-IF.
*----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 3020-SYSTEM-LOOP.
     DISPLAY INFO-03, SPACE, SYSTEM-NAME OF SYSTEM-TABLE (SYSTEM-INDEX).
* Obtain VERSION-INDEX for current system
     SET VERSION-INDEX TO 1.
     SEARCH VERSION-TABLE
         END
*            This should never occur !
             PERFORM
                 STRING COMPLETION-56     DELIMITED SIZE
                        " (version link)" DELIMITED SIZE
                        INTO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
                 MOVE 1 TO ABEND-REQUIRED-FLAG
                 PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
             END-PERFORM
         WHEN VERSION-VALUE (VERSION-INDEX) = SYSTEM-VERSION (SYSTEM-INDEX)
             NEXT SENTENCE
     END-SEARCH.
* Reset CPU-TABLE and PROCESS-TABLE
     MOVE ZERO TO CPU-MAX, PROCESS-MAX.
* Obtain CPU information
     DISPLAY FOUR-SPACES, INFO-06.
     PERFORM VARYING MEASURE-INDEX FROM 1 BY 1
           UNTIL MEASURE-INDEX > MEASURE-MAX
         IF MEASURE-VALID-FILE(MEASURE-INDEX) = "Y"
           IF MEASURE-SYSTEM-NUMBER (MEASURE-INDEX) = SYSTEM-INDEX
             PERFORM 3100-READ-CPU-INFO
           END-IF
         END-IF
     END-PERFORM.
* Fill in F02
     ADD CPU-MAX TO F02.
* Sort CPU-TABLE
     PERFORM 3140-CPU-TABLE-SORT.
* Obtain process information
     DISPLAY FOUR-SPACES, INFO-09.
     PERFORM VARYING MEASURE-INDEX FROM 1 BY 1
           UNTIL MEASURE-INDEX > MEASURE-MAX
         IF MEASURE-VALID-FILE(MEASURE-INDEX) = "Y"
           IF MEASURE-SYSTEM-NUMBER (MEASURE-INDEX) = SYSTEM-INDEX
              PERFORM 3300-READ-PROCESS-INFO
           END-IF
         END-IF
     END-PERFORM.
* Sort PROCESS-TABLE
     PERFORM 3370-PROCESS-TABLE-SORT.
* Insert PROCESS-UNIQUE
     PERFORM 3380-INSERT-PROCESS-UNIQUE.
* Obtain discopen information
     DISPLAY FOUR-SPACES, INFO-10.
     PERFORM 3400-READ-DISCOPEN-INFO
           VARYING MEASURE-INDEX FROM 1 BY 1
           UNTIL MEASURE-INDEX > MEASURE-MAX.
* This time we scan all measurement data files; this is because measurements
* taken on other systems might include DISCOPEN records related to processes
* on the current system
*----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 3100-READ-CPU-INFO.
* Get CPU information
     MOVE ZERO TO FIRSTCALL.
* Read CPU counter record blocks until FIRSTCALL is ZERO.
     PERFORM 3105-GET-CPU-DATA TEST AFTER UNTIL FIRSTCALL ZERO.
* Display debug fields
     IF DEBUG-MODE
         DISPLAY ">CPU-MAX: ", CPU-MAX
     END-IF.
*----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 3105-GET-CPU-DATA.
*------------MeasTCM Yosemite Change----Start-----------
     IF YOSEMITE-DATAFILE = "Y"
        ENTER TAL "MEASREAD_DIFF_"
        USING   MEASURE-DFNUM (MEASURE-INDEX),
             ALL-CPUS,
             MEASREAD-BUFFER,
             MEASREAD-BUFFER-LENGTH,
             BYTESRET,
             FIRSTCALL,
             MEAS-START,
             MEAS-STOP,
             OMITTED,
             SYSTEM-VERSION (SYSTEM-INDEX),
             OMITTED,
             ZERO,
             OMITTED,
             OMITTED,
             OMITTED,
             OMITTED,
             ZMSCPU-TEMPLATE-VERSION
        GIVING RESULT
     ELSE
*------------MeasTCM Yosemite Change-----End------------
        ENTER TAL "MEASREAD_DIFF_"
        USING   MEASURE-DFNUM (MEASURE-INDEX),
             ALL-CPUS,
             MEASREAD-BUFFER,
             MEASREAD-BUFFER-LENGTH,
             BYTESRET,
             FIRSTCALL,
             MEAS-START,
             MEAS-STOP,
             OMITTED,
             SYSTEM-VERSION (SYSTEM-INDEX),
             OMITTED,
             ZERO
        GIVING RESULT
*------------MeasTCM Yosemite Change----Start-----------
     END-IF.
*------------MeasTCM Yosemite Change-----End------------
     IF RESULT NOT ZERO
         MOVE RESULT TO NUMBER-DISPLAY
         STRING COMPLETION-52  DELIMITED SIZE
                SPACE          DELIMITED SIZE
                NUMBER-DISPLAY DELIMITED SIZE
                INTO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
         MOVE 1 TO ABEND-REQUIRED-FLAG
         PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
     END-IF.
     IF BYTESRET NOT ZERO
           PERFORM 3110-TREAT-CPU-INFO
     END-IF.
*----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 3110-TREAT-CPU-INFO.
* Treat CPU information according to measurement data version
*------------MeasTCM Yosemite Change----Start-----------
        IF YOSEMITE-DATAFILE = "Y"
* We use FUNCTION LENGTH() to calculate the length of ZMSCPU-DEFINITION as
* MEASGETVERSION() returns legacy style Entity lengths.
             DIVIDE FUNCTION LENGTH(ZMSCPU-DEFINITION) INTO BYTESRET
             MOVE ZERO TO ZMSCPU-CNTR-START
             SET ZMSCPU-PNTR TO ADDRESS OF MEASREAD-BUFFER
             PERFORM 3115-TREAT-CPU-ENTITY-Y
                VARYING ENTITY-COUNTER FROM 1 BY 1
                UNTIL   ENTITY-COUNTER > BYTESRET
        ELSE
*------------MeasTCM Yosemite Change-----End------------
             DIVIDE CPU-ENTITY-LENGTH OF VERSION-TABLE (VERSION-INDEX)
             INTO BYTESRET
             MOVE ZERO TO CPU-CNTR-START
             MOVE CPU-ENTITY-LENGTH OF VERSION-TABLE (VERSION-INDEX) TO CPU-CNTR-END
             SET CPU-PNTR TO ADDRESS OF MEASREAD-BUFFER
             PERFORM 3115-TREAT-CPU-ENTITY
                VARYING ENTITY-COUNTER FROM 1 BY 1
                UNTIL   ENTITY-COUNTER > BYTESRET
*------------MeasTCM Yosemite Change----Start-----------
        END-IF.
*------------MeasTCM Yosemite Change-----End------------
*----------------------------------------------------------------------------
** Any logical change in procedure 3115-TREAT-CPU-ENTITY could also apply
** to the equivalent procedure 3115-TREAT-CPU-ENTITY-Y. Please check.
 3115-TREAT-CPU-ENTITY.
* Set the addresses to point to the current entity.  Prepare PNTR for next one.
*     SET ADDRESS OF CPU-DEFINITION TO CPU-PNTR.
     MOVE MEASREAD-BUFFER( CPU-CNTR-START + 1  : FUNCTION LENGTH(CPU-DEFINITION) )   TO CPU-DEFINITION
     ADD CPU-CNTR-END      TO  CPU-CNTR-START
*    SET CPU-PNTR UP BY FUNCTION LENGTH(CPU-DEFINITION).
* Soln 10-000602-8415. Check for CONVERTTO and accordingly determine I10
* (the base CPU OS version) of  CSV-I-DATA, from the CPU-DEFINITION buffer.
* Changes start here.
     IF (((CPU-TYPE OF CPU-DEFINITION = TEMP-CPU-TYPE) AND
      (CPU-SUBTYPE OF CPU-DEFINITION = TEMP-CPU-SUBTYPE) AND CONVERTTO-PRESENT)
      OR (NOT CONVERTTO-PRESENT))     AND
      (CPU-TYPE-FLAG = 0 OR TEMP-OS-VERSION-Z < OS-VERSION OF CPU-DEFINITION)
* CPU-TYPE-FLAG is set to 1. So the latest OS version is taken as I10, when
* when measure files of different OS versions are present in this MeasTCM run.
            MOVE 1 TO CPU-TYPE-FLAG
            MOVE OS-VERSION OF CPU-DEFINITION TO TEMP-OS-VERSION-X
                                                 TEMP-OS-VERSION-Z
            MOVE VERSION-LETTER OF TEMP-OS-VERSION-Y TO VERSION-LETTER OF I10
            MOVE LOW-VALUES TO VERSION-LETTER OF TEMP-OS-VERSION-Y
            MOVE TEMP-OS-VERSION-X TO VERSION-NUMBER OF I10
     END-IF.
* Changes end here - Soln 10-000602-8415.
*    GAG.  IPM AAI.  Check if CPU record is valid.
     IF (FROM-TIMESTAMP OF CPU-DEFINITION + USEC-MINUTE) <
        MEASURE-START OF MEASURE-TABLE( MEASURE-INDEX)
      OR
        (TO-TIMESTAMP OF CPU-DEFINITION - USEC-MINUTE) >
          MEASURE-STOP OF MEASURE-TABLE (MEASURE-INDEX)
       DISPLAY INFO-25
       DISPLAY MEASURE-EXTERNAL-NAME (MEASURE-INDEX), " now marked invalid."
       MOVE INFO-25 TO CSV-TEMP-3
       MOVE "N" TO MEASURE-VALID-FILE (MEASURE-INDEX)
       MOVE 1 TO MEASURE-FILE-OVERFLOW
       MOVE ZERO TO BYTESRET, FIRSTCALL
     ELSE
       PERFORM 3115-00-CONTINUE-CPU-ENTITY
     END-IF.
*----------------------------------------------------------------------------
*------------MeasTCM Yosemite Change----Start-----------
** Any logical change in procedure 3115-TREAT-CPU-ENTITY-Y could also apply
** to the equivalent procedure 3115-TREAT-CPU-ENTITY. Please check.
 3115-TREAT-CPU-ENTITY-Y.
* Set the addresses to point to the current entity.  Prepare PNTR for next one.
*      SET ADDRESS OF ZMSCPU-DEFINITION TO ZMSCPU-PNTR.
       MOVE MEASREAD-BUFFER( ZMSCPU-CNTR-START + 1  : FUNCTION LENGTH(ZMSCPU-DEFINITION) )   TO ZMSCPU-DEFINITION
       ADD FUNCTION LENGTH(ZMSCPU-DEFINITION)      TO  ZMSCPU-CNTR-START
*      SET ZMSCPU-PNTR UP BY FUNCTION LENGTH(ZMSCPU-DEFINITION).
* Soln 10-000602-8415. Check for CONVERTTO and accordingly determine I10
* (the base CPU OS version) of  CSV-I-DATA, from the ZMSCPU-DEFINITION buffer.
* Changes start here.
      IF (((CPU-TYPE OF ZMSCPU-DEFINITION = TEMP-CPU-TYPE) AND
       (CPU-SUBTYPE OF ZMSCPU-DEFINITION = TEMP-CPU-SUBTYPE) AND CONVERTTO-PRESENT)
       OR (NOT CONVERTTO-PRESENT))     AND
       (CPU-TYPE-FLAG = 0 OR TEMP-OS-VERSION-Z < OS-VERSION OF ZMSCPU-DEFINITION)
* CPU-TYPE-FLAG is set to 1. So the latest OS version is taken as I10, when
* when measure files of different OS versions are present in this MeasTCM run.
             MOVE 1 TO CPU-TYPE-FLAG
             MOVE OS-VERSION OF ZMSCPU-DEFINITION TO TEMP-OS-VERSION-X
                                                  TEMP-OS-VERSION-Z
             MOVE VERSION-LETTER OF TEMP-OS-VERSION-Y TO VERSION-LETTER OF I10
             MOVE LOW-VALUES TO VERSION-LETTER OF TEMP-OS-VERSION-Y
             MOVE TEMP-OS-VERSION-X TO VERSION-NUMBER OF I10
      END-IF.
* Changes end here - Soln 10-000602-8415.
*    GAG.  IPM AAI.  Check if CPU record is valid.
      IF (FROM-TIMESTAMP OF ZMSCPU-DEFINITION + USEC-MINUTE) <
         MEASURE-START OF MEASURE-TABLE( MEASURE-INDEX)
       OR
