 3370-PROCESS-TABLE-SORT.
* Sort PROCESS-TABLE in ascending order according to PROCESS-SORT-KEY
* using the Heapsort algorithm
     COPY HEAPSORT REPLACING
         I       BY HEAP-I
         IR      BY HEAP-IR
         J       BY HEAP-J
         L       BY HEAP-L
         N       BY PROCESS-MAX
         INDEX-1 BY PROCESS-INDEX
         INDEX-2 BY PROCESS-INDEX-2
         TABLE   BY PROCESS-TABLE
         TEMP    BY PROCESS-TEMP
         KEY     BY PROCESS-SORT-KEY.
*----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 3380-INSERT-PROCESS-UNIQUE.
* Insert a value into PROCESS-UNIQUE To make every
* (PROCESS-CPU-NUM,PROCESS-PIN) occurence in PROCESS-TABLE unique.
* This allows us to use SEARCH ALL in linking discopens to processes.
     MOVE HIGH-VALUES TO PID-SAVE.
     PERFORM
         VARYING PROCESS-INDEX FROM 1 BY 1
         UNTIL PROCESS-INDEX > PROCESS-MAX
         IF PROCESS-PID (PROCESS-INDEX) = PID-SAVE
*            Since PROCESS-UNIQUE is a NATIVE-2 field, it can only go
*            up to 32767 ...
             IF UNIQUE-COUNTER >= 32767
                  STRING COMPLETION-56       DELIMITED SIZE
                         " (PROCESS-UNIQUE)" DELIMITED SIZE
                         INTO COMPLETION-MESSAGE
                  MOVE 1 TO ABEND-REQUIRED-FLAG
                  PERFORM 9010-SPCOMPLETION
             END-IF
             ADD 1 TO UNIQUE-COUNTER
             MOVE UNIQUE-COUNTER TO PROCESS-UNIQUE (PROCESS-INDEX)
         ELSE
             MOVE ZERO TO UNIQUE-COUNTER
             MOVE UNIQUE-COUNTER TO PROCESS-UNIQUE (PROCESS-INDEX)
             MOVE PROCESS-PID (PROCESS-INDEX) TO PID-SAVE
         END-IF
     END-PERFORM.
